INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 14 (Semester Course)','Case studies in international strategy',NULL,'Course content: ● Introduction to international strategies ● Group work on real cases in international strategy● Group presentations and discussions on real cases in international strategyIntroduction on Monday 15.09.2014Block course on Friday 26.09.2014 Briefing at Sika on Wednesday 08.10.2014Discussions of the groups with the lecturer on Monday 10.11.2014Group presentations in presence of the CEO of Sika on Friday 05.12.2014 There will be 3 working groups of 4 students for working on real cases','6620-0554','English','Grnig R.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'General objective:To be able to systematically approach an issue in international strategy and to produce a clear solutionSubgoals:● To have an overview of international strategy● To know important methodological approaches and to be able to apply them in a real case● To get the needed information through company documents, interviews and internet ● To carry out a strategic analysis and to propose a solution to a real issue● To present and justify analysis and proposition','Handouts with attachments','each year',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  15; Re-assessment 15',NULL,'oral exam: 50%group presentation: 50%The registration period on mySES for this course / seminar will be from September 1st 9h00  to October 3th 2014. The registration for this course / seminar also implies the registration to the assessment period.After October 3th 2014, you cannot register any more to the course / seminar nor withdraw from the course / seminary','15 Min.','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; Module 1: Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Management; Module 8: European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Module European Business 