INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SS 15 (Semester Course)','Asian Management (Study Trip to Bangkok)',NULL,'Given the high and still rising relevance of Asia as market and as location for production, the chair organises a study trip to Bangkok. At a local university (College of Management of Mahidol University CMMU), University lecturers give lectures on different topics of Asian Management (e.g. cross-cultural management, retailing and consumer behaviour, leadership, learning organizations, entrepreneurship in Asia) and executives from companies in Thailand will give presentations on practical issues. The programme will also include cultural activities.	The courses in Bangkok are scheduled for five days plus one week-end; events might also be scheduled for the evenings.Accommodation will be organised by the chair, the travel (flight, etc.) will have to be organised by the participants individually. There is a fee for the course (for the College in Thailand) and for accommodation. More details are announced on the webpage of the chair. http://www.unifr.ch/intman/teaching/current-semester/asian-management-2015','6620-0532','English','Morschett D.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'Providing students with knowledge, concepts and insights into business and management in Asia.','Readings will be announced by the chair.','every 2 years',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Summer 15; Re-assessment 15',NULL,'written exam: The requirements for the Master of Arts in European Business are listed in detail in the regulations (reglement). Previous knowledge of the subject is not required.No course enrollment at semester start.The registration period summer period 2015 for the exam will be from April 27th to May 8th 2015 on mySES.The registration period re-assessment period 2015 for the exam will be from July 13th to August 3th 2015 on mySES.	Without registration in the given period, no exam in the choosen period can be taken. Please take note of the deadline.','60 Min','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; Module 1: Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Management; Module 8: European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Module European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Module Strategic and General Management (STM) Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:16.017634','2017-05-06 13:27:16.017634');
