INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 14 (Semester Course)','Managing Organizational Change',NULL,'To  achieve these goals, we work toward building a conceptual foundation and a good working knowledge of the analytic  frameworks of organizational change management. You will have three opportunities to apply the frameworks:  First, we will spend time in class discussing  fundamental topics in organizational change management.  Session leadership in  teams: I will ask you in teams to take responsibility to  prepare and then lead a session on a given topic. Please note that for an  effective planning, your enrollment to a topic is mandatory by Sep 23 on  moodle. Teams and topics are allocated on a first-come first-serve basis. Your contributions are due by  the respectively scheduled session.  Company analysis teams will investigate in detail a real-world organizations challenge to  design and deliver organizational change. Teams written analyses and in-class  presentations will provide the capstone experience for the course. Teams and  topics will be finalized in our session with a strategic change practitioner  (previous guests include Arvato Services or Bombardier Transportation among  others). Your team presentations are due by the final session with our guest.','6620-0579','English','Jacobs C.',NULL,'Master',2,3.0,'This course focuses on the problems that organizations face in the  designing and implementing change. Research in the field of strategic and  organizational change management provides the intellectual basis for the  course; reading and discussing this literature will be a principle focus.  Problems require students to take the perspective of an analyst, designer and  manager of a strategic change program.The over-arching goal is to learn to conceptualize and design  organizational change challenges in a systematic, yet context-sensitive way.  Furthermore, the goals include:  Mastering core conceptual frameworks related to the  analysis and development of organizational change.  Developing skills in problem recognition and problem  solving.  Developing the ability to think and act as analyst,  designer and manager of an organizational change program.Topics of the course include among others (a complete  list with session topics will be provided in the kick-off session):  Organizational culture and context  Philosophies and theories of change  Change, strategy and leadership  Organizational identity  Sensemaking and sensegiving  Psychology and emotions of change  Politics of change and middle-management  Metaphors, narrative and rhetoric of change  Implementing and sustaining change','Course book: Balogun, J. and Hope Hailey, V. 2008. Exploring Strategic Change. 3rd ed. Prentice Hall','once',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  15; Re-assessment 15',NULL,'written exam: Company analysis teams and topics will be allocated in classNo course enrollment at semester start.The registration period winter period 2014 for the exam will be from December 1st  to December 12th 2014 on mySES.The registration period re-assessment period 2015 for the exam will be from July 13th to August 3th 2015 on mySES.	Without registration in the given period, no exam in the choosen period can be taken. Please take note of the deadline.','60 Min','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; Module 2: Organization and Human Resource Management (OHR) Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:16.251775','2017-05-06 13:27:16.251775');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 14 (Semester Course)','Mergers & Acquisitions',NULL,'The course covers several aspects of mergers & acquisitions. Starting with an empirical overview of M&A activity and success of M&A transactions.The course focuses on M&A deal design & reorganization and on deal financing.','6620-0543','English','Drr O.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'The course aims to provide a broad overview of merger & acquisitions.','Weston, J.F., Mitchell, M.L., Mulherin, J.H. (2004): Takeovers, restructuring, and corporate governance, 4th edition, UppersSaddleRiver.Bruner, Robert F. (2004): Applied Mergers & Acquisitions, Hoboken.Gaughan, Patrick A. (2011): Mergers, Acquisitions, and Corporate Restructurings, 5th Ed., Hoboken.','every 2 years',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  15; Re-assessment 15',NULL,'written examNo course enrollment at semester start.The registration period winter period 2014 for the exam will be from December 1st  to December 12th 2014 on mySES.The registration period re-assessment period 2015 for the exam will be from July 13th to August 3th 2015 on mySES.	Without registration in the given period, no exam in the choosen period can be taken. Please take note of the deadline.','60 Min','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; Module 4: Finance (FIN) Master in Management; Module 5: Accounting and Control (ACC) Master in Accounting and Finance; Module Accounting and Control (ACC) Master in Accounting and Finance; Module Finance (FIN) Master in European Business; Module Accounting and Control (ACC) Master in European Business; Module Finance (FIN) Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:16.255521','2017-05-06 13:27:16.255521');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SA 14 (cours semestriel)','Microéconomie I','Intermediate Microeconomics I','Consommation et production:Le cours porte sur les principaux facteurs de la consommation et de la production,  savoir la demande, l''offre, les interactions entre la demande et l''offre, les lasticits, la thorie du consommateur et la thorie du producteur (cots de production). Le cours est complt par des sances d''exercices ainsi que par des prsentations thmatiques qui portent sur des applications concrtes des donnes thoriques, notamment dans le domaine de la concurrence.','SEEP02A001','français','Gugler P.',NULL,'Bachelor',4,6.0,'Matrise des principaux facteurs de la consommation et de la production,  savoir la demande, l''offre, les interactions entre la demande et l''offre, les lasticits, la thorie du consommateur et la thorie du producteur (cots de production).','1. Gregory Mankiw, M. Taylor, Principes de l''conomie, de Boeck, 20112. N. Gregory Mankiw, M. Taylor, Economics, 20113a. Robert S. Pindyck et Daniel L. Rubinfeld, Microconomie, 6me dition, Pearson Education, 2005 (version anglaise galement disponible).3b. Robert S. Pindyck, J. Hamilton et V. Suslow, Guide de l''tudiant en Microconomie, 6me dition, Pearson Education, 2006.','chaque anne',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rglement du 19 mai 2014 sur l''organisation des tudes et des examens  la Facult des sciences conomiques et sociales de l''Universit de Fribourg','Hiver 15; Rattrapage 15','2015-01-09 08:30:00','épreuve écritePas d''inscription au cours au dbut du semestre.L''inscription  l''preuve de la session d''hiver 2015 a lieu du 1er dcembre au 12 dcembre 2014 sur mySES.L'' inscription  l''preuve de la session de rattrapage 2015 a lieu du 13 juillet au 3 aot 2015 sur mySES.	Sans inscription dans le dlai cit ci-dessus, l''preuve ne peut pas tre passe dans la session choisi. Veuillez imprativement respecter le dlai d''inscription aux preuves.','90','français','Valable pour les programmes suivant