INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 15 (Semester Course)','Case studies in international strategy',NULL,'Course content:● Introduction to internationalization and international strategy ● Approaches for going international for new markets● Example of a group presentation of a former year● Briefings● Group work on real cases in international strategy● Group presentations and discussions on real cases in international strategyProgram:● Introduction on Monday, 14.09.2015● Block course on Friday, 25.09.2015● Briefing from the company on Friday, 09.10.2015 ● Discussion of the groups with the lecturer on Friday, 06.11.2015● Group presentations on Friday, 04.12.2015There will be 3 working groups of 4 students','6620-0554','English','Grnig R.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'General objective:To be able to systematically approach an issue in international strategy and to produce a clear solutionSubgoals:● To have an overview of internationalization and of international strategy● To know important methodological approaches and to be able to apply them on a real case● To get the needed information through company documents, interviews and internet ● To carry out a strategic analysis and to propose a solution to a real issue● To present and justify analysis and proposition','● Outline● 2 handouts with attachments● Example of a group presentation of a former year● Document on oral exam with attachments','each year',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  16; Re-assessment 16',NULL,'Continuous evaluation + oral exam: 50%group presentation: 50%The registration period on mySES for this course / seminar will be from Wednesday 9th September 9h00  to Thursday 8th October 2015. The registration for this course / seminar also implies the registration to the assessment period.After Thursday 8th October 2015, you cannot register any more to the course /