INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 15 (Semester Course)','Applied Econometrics',NULL,'This course is an extension of the basic course Statistik II (statistics II). Building on the introductory econometric concepts of the latter, Applied Econometrics deals with econometric methods and their practical application in the presence of particular problems such as: 1) nonlinear models2) heteroscedasticity (non-constant variances of the residuals)3) non-random sampling4) measurement errors in variables5) omitted variables and endogeneity 6) time constant omitted variables (fixed effects) in panel dataAs practical illustration and for further intuition, the contents of the lecture are applied to real data in 5 PC lab sessions using the statistical software R. An introduction to R is provided in the first PC lab.','6630-0065','English','Huber M.',NULL,'Bachelor',3,4.5,'Students should be able to understand and practically apply the statistical/econometric models and methods discussed in the lecture.','Wooldridge, J. M. (2013): Introductory Econometrics. A Modern Approach, 5th edition, Cengage Learning.','each year',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  16; Re-assessment 16',NULL,'written exam: and participation in PC labsNo course enrollment at semester start.The registration period winter period 2016 for the exam will be from November 30th to December 11th 2015 on mySES.The registration period re-assessment period 2016 for the exam will be from July 25th to August 5th 2016 12:00 am on mySES.	Without registration in the given period, no exam in the choosen period can be taken. Please take note of the deadline.','90 Min','German; English','Valid for the following programmes: Bachelor in Economics; 27 ECTS cours en Économie politique Master in Economics; Module 6: Quantitative Economics Master in Economics; Offer Master list Econ