INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 15 (Semester Course)','Customer orientation and complaint management',NULL,'The course consists of several components:- theoretical component: discussion of theoretical approaches in the fields of customer satisfaction, complaint management, customer retention, and CRM- analytical component: showing the application of quantitative methods (e.g., regression analysis, ANOVA) in order to develop strategies in the field of customer satisfaction and retention - practical component: compiling the major issues of a professional complaint management on the basis of real examples from marketing practice (group work and presentation)- scientific component: going through selected scientific articles in the field of satisfaction, complaint and retention researchThe group work projects are a mandatory part of the course. The overall exam grade will be calculated as follows: 0.1* grade of the group work project + 0.9*grade of the written exam.','6620-0534','English','Bambauer-Sachse S.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'The purpose of this course is to discuss theoretical aspects of customer orientation and complaint management, to show the major issues of a professional complaint management through case study work and to explain how strategies can be developed on the basis of data analyses.','Kotler/Armstrong (2007): Principles of MarketingSolomon/Marshall/Stuart (2006): MarketingHomburg/Kuester/Krohmer (2009): Marketing ManagementDoole/Lancaster/Lowe (2005): Understanding and Managing CustomersBruhn (2003): Relationship MarketingEgan (2008): Relationship Marketing','every 2 years',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  16; Re-assessment 16',NULL,'written examNo course enrollment at semester start.The registration period winter period 2016 for the exam will be from November 30th to December 11th 2015 on mySES.The registration period re-assessment period 2016 for the exam will be from July 25th to August 5th 2016 12:00 am on mySES.	Without registration in the given period, no exam in the choosen period can be taken. Please take note of the deadline.','60 Min','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; Module 3: Marketing (MAR) Master in European Business; Module Marketing (MAR) Master in Informationsmanagement Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:16.468860','2017-05-06 13:27:16.468860');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SA 15 (cours semestriel)','Cours: Communication, organisation et e-Business','Course: Communication, organization and e-Business','Ce cours traite des volutions de la communication et des organisations lies au dveloppement des technologies de linformation et de la communication, et notamment dInternet. On rappellera les fondements thoriques permettant de cerner ces volutions et on examinera les nouvelles formes de mdiation qui se dveloppent avec les e-activits. Laccent sera mis sur les changements organisationnels et communicationnels dans le cadre du e-business. Les questions lies au e-marketing et  la cybercrise seront galement tudies.  This lecture analyses changes in communication and organizations related to the development of information and communication technology, more specifically Internet. Theoretical backgrounds which permit to understand these changes will be presented; then new forms of mediation which are developing with e-activities will be examined. We will insist on organizational and communicational changes in the framework of e-business. Questions related to e-marketing and cyber crisis will also be studied.','6640-1273','français','Bourgeois D.',NULL,'Master',2,3.0,'Objectifs du cours : ce cours a pour objectif de prsenter les grandes caractristiques des changements communicationnels et organisationnels, notamment lis  lessor dInternet et du e-business. Objectives of the course: this lecture aims at showing the main characteristics of the communicational and organizational changes, particularly linked to the development of Internet and e-business.',NULL,'chaque anne',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rglement du 19 mai 2014 sur l''organisation des tudes et des examens  la Facult des sciences conomiques et sociales de l''Universit de Fribourg','Hiver 16; Rattrapage 16','0001-03-19 14:00:00','Evaluation continue + épreuve écriteL''inscription  ce cours ou sminaire sur mySES a lieu du mercredi 9 septembre 9h00 au jeu