INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'HS 15 (Semesterkurs)','Master-Kolloquium','Research Seminar for Graduates','Sie stellen Ihr Forschungsprojekt zur Masterarbeit vor und diskutieren kritisch die zugrunde gelegten Theorien, das Forschungsinstrument, die Auswertung und Interpretation der Daten.','6640-0196','deutsch','Fahr A.',NULL,'Master',2,3.0,' Sie lernen, Ihre eigene Forschungsarbeit und die Arbeiten Ihrer Mitstudierenden kritisch zu beurteilen und weiterzuentwickeln. Sie ben, Ihre Ideen und Herangehensweisen fundiert zu begrnden und zu verteidigen sowie mit konstruktiv-kritischen Einwnden umzugehen.  Sie sind in der Lage, die Kohrenz und Qualitt einer wissenschaftlichen Arbeit zu analysieren und zu verbessern.','www.unifr.ch/dcm/index.php?page=lizentiatskolloquium','jedes Jahr',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Reglement vom 19. Mai 2014 der Examina an der Wirtschafts- und Sozialwissenschaftlichen Fakultt der Universitt Freiburg',NULL,NULL,'Fortlaufende Evaluation',NULL,'deutsch','Zählt für die folgenden Programme: Master in Kommunikationswissenschaft und Medienforschung; Kolloquium','2017-05-06 13:27:16.705503','2017-05-06 13:27:16.705503');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 15 (Semester Course)','Masterseminar: Social Media and Public Diplomacy: Challenges for international public relations in the digital era',NULL,'International public relations takes on many forms and functions for organizations of all kinds. In times of globalization and the web 2.0, a major function of PR involves the management of an organizations relationships with a variety of stakeholders spread across different offline, online, national and cultural environments. Therefore, the strategic organization of PR in the multinational environment, its opportunities, boundaries and challenges are at the heart of international PR research.In our seminar, we will first address the different research streams forming the body of international PR to gain a general understanding about its concepts and applications. Afterwards, we will focus on three aspects of international PR: (1) public diplomacy (key concepts, practices and current challenges in the digital era) and (2) corporate international PR on social media applications (strategic relevance, organizational application and user motivations). Finally, we will have a look at (3) the role culture plays in international PR and explore the implications of cultural values/variables on international PR (on the Web 2.0 and public diplomacy).Students will gain substantial knowledge about theoretical and practical approaches to international PR in an offline and online environment from a macro, meso, as well as the individuals micro-perspective. By focusing on different aspects of international PR, students will acquire insights which will help them address research questions to be further elaborated on in their term papers. During the course, students will be given the opportunity to work on their research proposals, and discuss their research ideas within the class.','6640-1583','English','Ingenhoff D.',NULL,'Master',2,3.0,'By focusing on different aspects of international PR, students will acquire insights which will help them address research questions to be further elaborated on in their term papers. During the course, students will be given the opportunity to work on their research proposals, and discuss their research ideas within the class.',NULL,'-',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'Continuous evaluationThe registration period on mySES for this course / seminar will be from Wednesday 9th September 9h00  to Thursday 8th October 2015. The registration for this course / seminar also implies the registration to the assessment period.After Thursday 8th October 2015, you cannot register any more to the course / seminar nor withdraw from the course / seminary',NULL,'English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Communication and Media Research; IV. Rezeptions- und Wirkungsforschung Master in Communication and Media Research; Modul B «Journalism and Organizational Communication» Master in Communication and Media Research; V. Organisationskommunikation und Public Relations','2017-05-06 13:27:16.708305','2017-05-06 13:27:16.708305');
