INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 15 (Semester Course)','Swiss Living Challenge  Seminar',NULL,'Der Schweizer Energie-Sektor befindet sich im Wandel. Derzeit ist eine grosse Unsicherheit im Markt zu spren und umfangreiche Vernderungen zeichnen sich ab. Stichworte hierzu sind: Versorgungssicherheit als Rahmenbedingung, Energiestrategie 2050, marktwirtschaftlicher Wettbewerb in Netzen, fortschreitende Marktffnung, technischer Wandel durch Smart Grids. Einfhrung und Aufbau von Kompetenzen zur Planung und Steuerung von im Energiesektor agierenden Unternehmen.','6650-0169','English','Teufel S.',NULL,'Master',2,3.0,'Einfhrung und Aufbau von Kompetenzen zur Planung und Steuerung von im Energiesektor agierenden Unternehmen.','werden im Kurs bekanntgegeben','once',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  16; Re-assessment 16',NULL,'oral examNo course enrollment at semester start.The registration period winter period 2016 for the exam will be from November 30th to December 11th 2015 on mySES.The registration period re-assessment period 2016 for the exam will be from July 25th to August 5th 2016 12:00 am on mySES.	Without registration in the given period, no exam in the choosen period can be taken. Please take note of the deadline.','15 Min','German; English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; Module 1: Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Management; Module 6: Information and Communication Technology (ICT) Master in European Business; Module Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Information Management; ICT: Information and Communication Technology Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:16.813651','2017-05-06 13:27:16.813651');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 15 (Semester Course)','Sustainable Globalization',NULL,'Globalization comes in many forms: final goods trade, international outsourcing, international capital flows, international migration of labor, international protection of intellectual property, and international technology transfer. There are a variety of concerns associated with these fundamental changes. Critics argue that some of these patterns affect the sustainability of economic and human development in an undesired fashion. For instance, does liberalization of goods trade and financial markets harm the environment and promote child labor in developing countries? Does international outsourcing of production enhance economic insecurity of workers? Does international migration harm developing countries by triggering brain drain? Does immigration in advanced countries lead to more crime and higher housing costs?','6610-0499','English','Spring E.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'The goal of the seminar is to obtain a deeper understanding of the consequences of globalization for sustainable economic and human development. We aim at a close connection between theoretical hypotheses and empirical evidence on causal relationships.','www.unifr.ch/makro','each year',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'Continuous evaluation: Die Notenvergabe erfolgt aufgrund der Leistungen in der mndlichen Mitarbeit (20 Prozent der Gesamtnote), einer schriftlichen Seminararbeit (40 Prozent der Gesamtnote) und einem Vortrag whrend des Seminars (40 Prozent der Gesamtnote).Im Falle einer ungengenden Note muss das Seminar komplett wiederholt werden.The registration period on mySES for this course / seminar will be from Wednesday 9th September 9h00  to Thursday 8th October 2015. The registration for this course / seminar also implies the registration to the assessment period.After Thursday 8th October 2015, you cannot register any more to the course / seminar nor withdraw from the course / seminary',NULL,'English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; Module 2: Economic Policy Master in Economics; Module 3: Economic Sustainability and Development Master in Economics; Module 5: International Economics Master in Economics; Offer Master list Economics Master in Economics; Specialization QM&ET: Module I.3 Macroeconomic Theory Master in Management; Module 8: European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Module European Business (EUB) Master in Economics; Specialization Ethics and Economics; Module II : conomie et thique Ethics and Economics: 30 ECTS Minor Master; Module II : conomie et thique Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:16.816156','2017-05-06 13:27:16.816156');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SP 16 (cours semestriel)','Communication appliquée','Communication in practice','Acqurir des connaissances thoriques et pratiques pour concevoir et raliser des campagnes de communication. Ltudiant devra ensuite proposer des projets sur la base de cas dtude, selon plusieurs tapes:- analyse du contexte gnral et communicationnel; le diagnostic- choix du positionnement et des cibles- laboration de largumentaire- choix, planification et ralisation des actions de communication- bilan critique des intrts et limites des solutions proposes','6640-1438','français','Cauhp F.',NULL,'Master',2,3.0,'Comment concevoir et raliser des projets de campagne d''informations et de communication de la phase d''analyse  la phase de production et de diffusion, sur la base de cas d''tude.','-La Communication institutionnelle; Priv/Public, le manuel des stratgies, Eric Giuily, PUF, 2010-Le Plan de communication, Thierry Libaert, Dunod, 3me dition, 2008- Communication  des entreprises, Stratgies et Pratiques, Liliane Demont-Lugol, Alain Kempf, Martine Rapidel, Charles Scibetta, Armand Colin, 2me dition, 2013','chaque anne',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Rglement du 19 mai 2014 sur l''organisation des tudes et des examens  la Facult des sciences conomiques et sociales de l''Universit de Fribourg','Et 16; Rattrapage 16','2016-06-16 17:00:00','Evaluation continue + épreuve écriteL''inscription  ce cours ou sminaire sur mySES a lieu du 18 fvrier 9h00 au vendredi 18 mars 2016.	Aprs le vendredi 18 mars 2016, vous ne pourrez plus vous inscrire  cette preuve ou vous desinscrire de cette preuve.','60 Min','français','Valable pour les programmes suivants: Master in Business Communication','2017-05-06 13:27:16.818728','2017-05-06 13:27:16.818728');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 15 (Semester Course)','Strategic Value Creation',NULL,'By integrating thinking from strategic management and innovation theory, the course will explore three core questions:1) What kind of value should companies aim for?2) How can companies capture value by transforming organizations, starting new ventures and collaborating with other organizations?3) How can companies sustain value by executing strategies, creating incentive structures and interacting in networks?The course enrolment is on mySES from 03.09.2012 9h00 - 28.09.2012.','6620-0244','English','Hilb M.',NULL,'Master',2,3.0,'The ability to understand the link between strategy and value creation has become crucial to succeeding in todays business world. The course is designed to provide students with the insights from strategy theory to better understand how companies create strategic value. Upon completion of the course, the participants should be prepared to act on this understanding and support organizations in developing and implementing value-driven strategies.','www.strategydialogue.com','each year',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'Continuous evaluation: - Report (50%)- Presentation (30%)- Class Quizes (20%)The registration period on mySES for this course / seminar will be from Wednesday 9th September 9h00  to Thursday 8th October 2015. The registration for this course / seminar also implies the registration to the assessment period.After Thursday 8th October 2015, you cannot register any more to the course / seminar nor withdraw from the course / seminary',NULL,'English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; Module 1: Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Management; Module 8: European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Module European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Module Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Informationsmanagement Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:16.822113','2017-05-06 13:27:16.822113');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 15 (Semester Course)','Supply Chain Management & Logistics',NULL,'The main part of the course is about solution methods for supplier selection, warehouse location, demand forecasting, master planning, purchasing planning, operations scheduling, and vehicle routing. The course will contain an Operations Research primer (formulation of linear, nonlinear and integer programs; solution with Excel Solver-Add-In).','6650-0118','English','Widmer M.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'This course considers the various aspects of the supply chain management (SCM), which lets an organization get the right goods and services to the place they are needed at the right time, in the proper quantity and at an acceptable cost. Efficiently managing this process involves overseeing relationships with suppliers and customers, controlling inventory, forecasting demand and getting constant feedback on what is happening at every link in the chain.','http://moodle2.unifr.ch/','each year',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  16; Re-assessment 16',NULL,'written exam: documents of the course, personal notes, exercises, calculatorNo course enrollment at semester start.The registration period winter period 2016 for the exam will be from November 30th to December 11th 2015 on mySES.The registration period re-assessment period 2016 for the exam will be from July 25th to August 5th 2016 12:00 am on mySES.	Without registration in the given period, no exam in the choosen period can be taken. Please take note of the deadline.','90 minutes','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; Module 1: Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Management; Module 2: Organization and Human Resource Management (OHR) Master in European Business; Module Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Information Management; DS-AS: Decision Support and Applied Statistics Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:16.827058','2017-05-06 13:27:16.827058');
