INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 15 (Semester Course)','Risk Management and Financial Derivatives',NULL,'This course deals with measuring and managing financial risks. We analyze how risk management creates value for non-financial and financial institutions, and how valuable risk management strategies can be devised. The focus of the course is not on derivative valuation or technicalities but on the use of derivative instruments. We look at risk management from the perspective of managers rather than traders. Part of the course is based on Excel case studies.','SEGE02A023','English','Wallmeier M.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'The course enables students to analyze risk and to devise appropriate risk mangement strategies.','Will be given in the first session.','-',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  16; Re-assessment 16',NULL,'written examNo course enrollment at semester start.The registration period winter period 2016 for the exam will be from November 30th to December 11th 2015 on mySES.The registration period re-assessment period 2016 for the exam will be from July 25th to August 5th 2016 12:00 am on mySES.	Without registration in the given period, no exam in the choosen period can be taken. Please take note of the deadline.','90 Min','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; Module 9: Finance Master in Economics; Specialization QM&ET: Module II.1 Microeconomics Master in Economics; Module 9: Finance Master in Economics; Specialization QM&ET: Module II.1 Microeconomics Master in Management; Module 4: Finance (FIN) Master in Accounting and Finance; Module Finance (FIN) Master in European Business; Module Finance (FIN) Master in Informationsmanagement','2017-05-06 13:27:16.849605','2017-05-06 13:27:16.849605');
