INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SS 16 (Semester Course)','Monetary theory and policy III: Theoretical foundations of monetary analysis',NULL,'Ire partie: Nature, fonctions et valeur de la monnaieIIme partie: Macroconomie montaireIIIme partie: Banques et paiements','6610-0289','English','Rossi S.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'Donner aux tudiant-e-s les lments ncessaires pour une comprhension solide de la thorie montaire traditionnelle et contemporaine.Donner aux tudiant-e-s les outils danalyse des questions montaires de lpoque moderne en ce qui concerne les systmes de paiement et de rglement, nationaux et transfrontires.','Rossi, S. (2008) Macroconomie montaire: thories et politiques, Bruxelles, Paris et Zrich: Bruylant, LGDJ et Schulthess.Une liste de rfrences bibliographiques sera distribue lors du premier cours.','every 2 years',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Summer 16; Re-assessment 16',NULL,'oral exam: Aucun moyen n''est autorisThe registration period summer period 2016 for the exam will be from 18th February 9h00  to Friday 18th Mars 2016 on mySES.The registration period re-assessment period 2016 for the exam will be from July 25th to August 5th 2016 12:00 am on mySES.	Without registration in the given period, no exam in the choosen period can be taken. Please take note of the deadline.','15 Min','French; German; English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; Module 7: Economic Theory Master in Economics; Offer Master list Economics Master in Economics; Specialization QM&ET: Module I.3 Macroeconomic Theory Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.194200','2017-05-06 13:27:17.194200');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SS 16 (Semester Course)','Policy and Impact Evaluation',NULL,'This course discusses econometric tools for assessing the causal impact of some policy intervention (also referred to as treatment) on an outcome of interest. This may, for instance, concern the effectiveness of public policies (e.g. training programs for unemployed, income support for poor families, public childcare,), corporate policies (marketing campaigns, educational programs for employees,), health interventions (new medical treatments), among many other examples. The following topics are covered:- The definition of causal effects (using the potential outcome notation)- Methods for policy and impact evaluation under exogeneity: estimation based on regression, matching, and weighting- Methods for policy and impact evaluation under endogeneity: estimation based on instruments, regression discontinuities and kinks, differences in differences, and changes in changes  - Methods for assessing causal mechanisms underlying a particular causal effect (mediation analysis)The lecture is accompanied by 4 PC sessions based on the software package R, in which the methods are applied to empirical data.','6610-0519','English','Huber M.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'Students should understand the intuition of the econometric methods discussed as well as the circumstances under which they can(not) be used to assess the causal impact of a particular policy. Furthermore, students should be able to practically apply the methods to real world data in order to conduct causal analyses.','reading list of selected papers','every 2 years',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Summer 16; Re-assessment 16',NULL,'written exam: and participation in PC sessionsThe registration period summer period 2016 for the exam will be from 18th February 9h00  to Friday 18th Mars 2016 on mySES.The registration period re-assessment period 2016 for the exam will be from July 25th to August 5th 2016 12:00 am on mySES.	Without registration in the given period, no exam in the choosen period can be taken. Please take note of the deadline.','90','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; Module 2: Economic Policy Master in Economics; Module 6: Quantitative Economics Master in Economics; Module 8: Industrial Organization Master in Economics; Offer Master list Economics Master in Economics; Specialization QM&ET: Module II.2 Advanced Econometrics Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.196859','2017-05-06 13:27:17.196859');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'FS 16 (Semesterkurs)','Info V: Decision Support II (d)','Decision Support II','In dieser Lehrveranstaltung werden quantitative Methoden des Operations Research zur Entscheidungsuntersttzung behandelt. Im ersten Teil werden Algorithmen zur Optimierung in Graphen und Netzwerken (Minimalgerste, Krzeste Wege, Zeitplanung in Projektnetzwerken) behandelt. Im zweiten Teil erfolgt eine Einfhrung in die Kombinatorische Optimierung anhand des Handlungsreisendenproblems. Im dritten Teil werden ausgewhlte Themen der Nichtlinearen und der Dynamischen Optimierung sowie der Simulation vorgestellt. Die Vorlesungsinhalte werden in bungen und Fallstudien vertieft; dabei wird auch Microsoft Excel zur Lsung von Optimierungsproblemen sowie zur Simulation eingesetzt.','SEIG02B008','deutsch','Trautmann N.',NULL,'Bachelor',3,4.5,'Keine Informationen vorhanden','Die Unterlagen zur Vorlesung werden via MOODLE bereitgestellt. Ergnzende Literatur:1) Domschke Drexl Klein Scholl (2015): Einfhrung in Operations Research. Springer2) Hillier Lieberman (2015): Operations Research. McGraw-Hill3) Neumann Morlock (2002): Operations Research. Hanser','jedes Jahr',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Reglement vom 19. Mai 2014 der Examina an der Wirtschafts- und Sozialwissenschaftlichen Fakultt der Universitt Freiburg','Sommer 16; Wiederholung 16','2016-06-16 08:30:00','schriftliche PrüfungDie Prfungseinschreibung Sommersession 2016 findet vom 18. Februar 9h00  Freitag 18. Mrz 2016 auf mySES statt.Die Prfungseinschreibung Wiederholungssession 2016 findet vom 25. Juli bis 5. August 12:00 2016 auf mySES statt.	Ohne Einschreibung in der genannten Frist knnen keine Prfungen in der gewhlten Session abgelegt werden. Bitte merken Sie sich den Termin unbedingt vor.','90 Min','französisch; deutsch','Zählt für die folgenden Programme: Bachelor in Wirtschaftsinformatik Wirtschaftsinformatik: Bachelornebenfach (60 ECTS) Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.2