INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 16 (Semester Course)','Advanced Managerial Accounting',NULL,'Formerly Dezentrale Unternehmenssteuerung:Management accountants provide managers with cost accounting data for effective decision-making, planning and controlling.This course builds on previous courses on management accounting from the bachelor program and covers more advanced topics such as different budgeting and transfer pricing methods.Besides illustrating specific management accounting techniques a special emphasis is placed on the development of analytical skills. In order to foster this, Monte Carlo simulation techniques are introduced to demonstrate how more accurate cost predictions can be derived leading to enhanced decision-making and cost control.Students will be encouraged to discuss the results of excel based exercises in class and to participate in a business case on management accounting.','SEGE02A024','English','Burkert M.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'This course is supposed to deepen the students understanding of management accounting methods and their role for effective managerial decision-making. Students are enabled to critically evaluate the validity of cost information and to dig behind the numbers.','Will be announced at the beginning of the course','every 2 years','Date Hour Course / Excercise Room Wednesday 21.09.2016 15:15 - 18:00 Course PER 21 A230 Wednesday 28.09.2016 15:15 - 19:00 Course PER 21 A230 Wednesday 05.10.2016 15:15 - 18:00 Course PER 21 A230 Wednesday 12.10.2016 15:15 - 19:00 Course PER 21 A230 Wednesday 19.10.2016 15:15 - 19:00 Course PER 21 A230 Wednesday 26.10.2016 15:15 - 18:00 Course PER 21 A230 Wednesday 09.11.2016 15:15 - 18:00 Course PER 21 A230 Wednesday 16.11.2016 15:15 - 18:00 Course PER 21 A230 Wednesday 23.11.2016 15:15 - 18:00 Course PER 21 A230 Wednesday 30.11.2016 15:15 - 18:00 Course PER 21 A230 Wednesday 07.12.2016 15:15 - 18:00 Course PER 21 A230 Wednesday 14.12.2016 15:15 - 20:00 Course PER 21 A230 Wednesday 21.12.