INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 16 (Semester Course)','Case studies in international strategy',NULL,'Course content:● Introduction to internationalization and international strategy ● Process for developing a growth strategy for a region● Example of a group presentation of a former year● Briefings● Group work on real cases in international strategy● Group presentations and discussions on real cases in international strategyProgram:● Introduction on Tuesday, 27.09.2016● Block course on Friday, 30.09.2016● Briefing from the company on Thursday, 06.10.2016 ● Discussion of the groups with the lecturer on Friday, 04.11.2016● Group presentations on Friday, 02.12.2016There will be 3 working groups of 4 students','6620-0554','English','Grnig R.','Blanc A.  Email : amandine.blanc@unifr.ch','Master',3,4.5,'General objective:To be able to systematically approach an issue in international strategy and to produce a clear solutionSubgoals:● To have an overview of international strategy● To know important methodological approaches and to be able to apply them in a real case● To get the needed information through company documents, interviews and internet ● To carry out a strategic analysis and to propose a solution to a real issue● To present and justify analysis and proposition','● Outline● Grnig, R., Morschett, D. (2017): Developing International Strategies, Second edition, Springer Berlin and Heidelberg● 2 handouts● Example of a group presentation of a former year','each year','Date Hour Course / Excercise Room Tuesday 27.09.2016 8:15 - 9:00 Seminar PER 21 D130 Friday 30.09.2016 8:15 - 18:00 Seminar PER 21 C130 Thursday 06.10.2016 8:15 - 18:00 Seminar Friday 04.11.2016 8:15 - 14:00 Seminar Friday 02.12.2016 8:15 - 22:00 Seminar','12','Not authorised','t','Erasmus students are not admitted to courses / seminaries with limited number of participants, unless exception granted by the professor at the request of the student.','Selection criteria:1. Readiness to work together with other students on a real case in international strategy2. Student of the Master in European Business3. Advancement in the study4. Inscription dateThe criteria are applied in the above mentioned order. This means that criteria 2 is only applied if the selection based on criteria 1 still gives more than 12 students, etc.Application on mySESApplication period: 15.09.16-25.09.16','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  17; Re-assessment 17',NULL,'Continuous evaluation + oral exam: 50%group presentation: 50%The registration period on mySES for this course / seminar will be from September 15th 9h00  to October 14th 2016 12:00 am. After October 14th 2016 12:00 am, you cannot register any more to the exam or cancel this  exam.','15 Min.','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; Module 8: Industrial Organization Master in Management; Module 1: Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Management; Module 8: European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Module European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Module Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Informationsmanagement Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.270871','2017-05-06 13:27:17.270871');
