INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 16 (Semester Course)','Consumer Research',NULL,'This course consists of two major parts. The first part aims to provide theoretical as well as methodological approaches in the field of consumer research. The objective of the second part is to work on small research projects in groups of several students and to give presentations on the conducted research. The research projects are a mandatory part of the course. The overall exam note will be calculated as follows: 0.2*research project grade + 0.8*grade of the written exam.','6620-0432','English','Bambauer-Sachse S.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'The purpose of this course is to provide theoretical approaches and to show the application of quantitative methods in the field of consumer behavior.','Schiffman/Kanuk: Consumer BehaviorSolomon/Bamossy/Askegaard/Hogg: Consumer Behavior','every 2 years','Date Hour Course / Excercise Room Monday 19.09.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 C230 Monday 26.09.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 C230 Monday 03.10.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 C230 Monday 10.10.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 C230 Monday 17.10.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 C230 Monday 24.10.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 C230 Monday 07.11.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 C230 Monday 14.11.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 C230 Monday 21.11.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 F230 Monday 21.11.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 B230 Monday 28.11.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 C230 Monday 05.12.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 C230 Monday 12.12.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 C230 Monday 19.12.2016 11:15 - 14:00 Course PER 21 C230','No restriction','Not authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  17; Re-assessment 17',NULL,'written exam: non-programmable calculatorThe registration period winter period 2017 for the exam will be from September 15th 