INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 16 (Semester Course)','Supply Chain Management & Logistics',NULL,'The main part of the course is about solution methods for supplier selection, warehouse location, demand forecasting, master planning, inventory management, and vehicle routing. The course will contain an Operations Research primer (formulation of linear, nonlinear and integer programs; solutionwith Excel Solver-Add-In).','6650-0118','English','Widmer M.','Venteicher F.  Email : francesca.venteicher@unifr.ch','Master',3,4.5,'This course considers the various aspects of the supply chain management (SCM), which lets an organization get the right goods and services to the place they are needed at the right time, in the proper quantity and at an acceptable cost. Efficiently managing this process involves overseeing relationships with suppliers and customers, controlling inventory, forecasting demand and getting constant feedback on what is happening at every link in the chain.','http://moodle2.unifr.ch/','each year','Day Hour Course / Excercise Frequency Room Wednesday 11:15 - 12:00 Exercises weekly PER 21 E140 Wednesday 13:15 - 15:00 Course weekly PER 21 E140','No restriction','Not authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  17; Re-assessment 17',NULL,'written exam: documents of the course, personal notes, exercises, calculatorThe registration period winter period 2017 for the exam will be from September 15th 09:00 to October 14th 2016 12:00 am on mySES.The examinations registration period for the re-assessment period 2017 will be open on mySES from 24th July to 4th August 2017, 12:00 am.	Without registration in the given period, no exam in the choosen period can be taken. Please take note of the deadline.','90 minutes','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; Module 1: Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Management; Module 2: Organization and Human Resource Management (OHR) Master in European Business; Module Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Information Management; DS-AS: Decision Support and Applied Statistics Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.431143','2017-05-06 13:27:17.431143');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SA 16 (cours semestriel)','Télévision et vidéo en ligne (II)','Television and online Video','Ce cours est tourn vers la pratique et propose aux tudiants de raliser leur propre reportage en suivant le parcours classique de la construction d''un sujet tlvis: tournage, criture du commentaire et montage, pose de voix, puis mise en ligne. Se rendre sur le terrain, camra au poing, permet d''tre  confront  des situations concrtes de tournage. Rdiger le commentaire forme  l''criture audiovisuelle. Un logiciel permet ensuite de monter son propre sujet. Il suffit de regarder le succs du support vido, pour se rendre compte que la capacit  crer un produit audiovisuel constitue aujourd''hui un atout fortement valoris.','6640-1353','français','Zimmerli V.',NULL,'Bachelor',2,3.0,'Former l''tudiant  construire un reportage tlvis: apprendre les codes pour l''criture d''un produit audiovisuel, se rendre sur le terrain pour recueillir des images et monter son sujet.','Mouriquand Jacques, Pratique du documentaire tlvis, Victoires Editions, 2004Besse Brigite, Desmormeaux Didier, Construire le reportage tlvis, Victoires Editions, 2011Manier Paul-Stphane, Le journalisme audiovisuel: les techniques rdactionnelles en tlvision et sur Internet, INA, 2011','chaque anne','Date Heure Cours / Excercice Salle Vendredi 30.09.2016 9:15 - 13:00 Cours PER 21 G120 Vendredi 07.10.2016 9:15 - 13:00 Cours PER 21 F0103 Vendredi 14.10.2016 9:15 - 13:00 Cours PER 21 F0103 Vendredi 28.10.2016 9:15 - 13:00 Cours PER 21 F0103 Vendredi 11.11.2016 9:15 - 13:00 Cours PER 21 F0103 Vendredi 25.11.2016 9:15 - 13:00 Cours PER 21 F0103 Vendredi 16.12.2016 9:15 - 13:00 Cours PER 21 G120','20','Pas autorisés','t','Etudiants Erasmus pas admis au cours / sminaires avec un nombre limit de participants, sauf si exception accorde par le professeur sur demande de ltudiant.','Toutes les inscriptions vont tre sur la liste d''attente.Le dpartement communication et des mdias va dcider qui peut su