INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SS 17 (Semester Course)','Business, Ethics, and Risk',NULL,'This course introduces students to business ethics, its theoretical foundations, and its practical applications, particularly in the area of risk.The course starts with an introduction to business ethics and risk theory. The main part then consists of practicing the skills of ethical thinking by examining a range of applied issues, such as environmental risks, bankruptcy, or gender perspectives. There is some space for topics suggested by students.Sessions will consist of a lecture, plenary discussion and group discussion. For seven of the sessions, students are asked to provide a one-page criticism of a paper to be read in advance','6610-0548','English','Roser D.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'The course has two sets of goals:1. Knowledge about ethics, business ethics, risk ethics, and the applied cases discussed in the course.2. Developing a good sense for spotting ethical questions, practicing critical thinking, and presenting practically relevant answers to the questions in a clear fashion.','Beauchamp, T., Arnold, D., and Bowie, N. (eds.)(2009). Ethical Theory and Business (Upper Saddle River N.J.: Pearson/Prentice Hall).Roeser,  S., Hillerbrand, R., Peterson, M., and Sandin, P. (eds.) (2013), Essentials of Risk Theory (Dordrecht: Springer)Rosenstand, N. (2012). The Moral of the Story: An Introduction to Ethics (New York: McGraw-Hill).','every 2 years','Day Hour Course / Excercise Frequency Room Tuesday 12:15 - 15:00 Course weekly PER 21 A120','No restriction','Authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Summer 17; Re-assessment 17',NULL,'Continuous evaluation + written examThe registration period on mySES for this course / seminar will be from 16h February 9h00  to Mars 17th 2017 12:00 am. After Mars 17th 2017 12:00 am, you cannot register any more to the exam or cancel this  exam.','60 Min','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; Module 4: Business Ethics and Social Responsibility Master in Management; Module 1: Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in European Business; Module Strategic and General Management (STM) Ethics and Economics: 30 ECTS Minor Master; Module I : thique et droits humains Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.590075','2017-05-06 13:27:17.590075');
