INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 16 (Semester Course)','Philosophical Foundations of Economic Thought',NULL,'Philosophical reflection takes the form of stepping back from our own thoughts and actions and asking ourselves: What do we mean by such-and-such? or What are we doing when we are doing such-and-such?In this course we will be engaging in philosophical reflection on some of the central concepts in economics, such as value, preference, rationality, action, transaction, externalities, and the market. We will do so through a careful reading of a selection of classical and contemporary readings from both philosophically inclined economists and economically informed philosophers. You will walk away with a deeper understanding of what you are doing when you are doing economics.','6610-0545','English','Glser M.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'Philosophical investigation of key concepts in economic thought. No prerequisites, other than a mindset of curiosity about your own discipline.','TBA','-','Date Hour Course / Excercise Room Thursday 22.09.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Course PER 21 A403 Thursday 29.09.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Course PER 21 A403 Thursday 06.10.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Course PER 21 A403 Thursday 13.10.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Course PER 21 G414 Thursday 20.10.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Course PER 21 A403 Thursday 27.10.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Course PER 21 A403 Thursday 03.11.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Course PER 21 A403 Thursday 10.11.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Course PER 21 A403 Thursday 17.11.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Course PER 21 A403 Thursday 24.11.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Course PER 21 A403 Thursday 01.12.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Course PER 21 A403 Thursday 15.12.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Course PER 21 A403 Thursday 22.12.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Course PER 21 A403','No restriction','Authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'Continuous evaluation: (take-home exam at the end of the semester)The registration period on mySES for this course / seminar will be from September 15th 9h00  to October 14th 2016 12:00 am. After October 14th 2016 12:00 am, you cannot register any more to the exam or cancel this  exam.',NULL,'English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; Module 4: Business Ethics and Social Responsibility Master in Economics; Offer Master list Economics Ethics and Economics: 30 ECTS Minor Master; Module I : thique et droits humains Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.640889','2017-05-06 13:27:17.640889');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 16 (Semester Course)','Master lecture Comparing Media Landscapes',NULL,'The term media landscape refers to the distinctive features of the media in any given country. But how can we explain differences and similarities between different media landscapes? How can we explain the quality of TV programs or newspapers we watch and read? How can we explain the fact that only very few successful private television stations exist in small states like Switzerland but so many strong TV companies in bigger neighboring countries? To modify Bill Clintons famous dictum: Its the structures, stupid!. Media structures go a long way towards explaining media performance. Comparative analyses of media landscapes are essential to better understand the conditions under which media content is produced. This lecture serves as an introduction and immersion into comparative media and communication research. It not only offers an overview of comparatives approaches in various research fields but also focuses on research in different world regions.','6640-1520','English','Puppis M.','Castro Herrero L.  Email : laia.castroherrero@unifr.ch','Master',2,3.0,'1) You will become acquainted with basic theoretical and methodological approaches for analyzing media and communication in a comparative perspective.2) You will gain an overview of relevant and topical research comparing various aspects of media landscapes and of media and communication research in different world regions.3) You will be able to critically assess existing studies and to discuss their contribution to communication research and practice.','A reader will be available at the beginning of the semester.','each year','Day Hour Course / Excercise Frequency Room Thursday 10:15 - 12:00 Course weekly PER 21 E130','No restriction','Not authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'Continuous evaluation: Essay/PaperThe registration period on mySES for this course / seminar will be from September 15th 9h00  to October 14th 2016 12:00 am. After October 14th 2016 12:00 am, you cannot register any more to the exam or cancel this  exam.',NULL,'English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Communication and Media Research; Basismodul «Theories, Methods and Research Fields» Master in Communication and Media Research; I. Allgemeine und systematische Kommunikationswissenschaft Master in Communication and Media Research; VI. Journalismus','2017-05-06 13:27:17.643779','2017-05-06 13:27:17.643779');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'HS 16 (Semesterkurs)','Praxiskurs Grundlagen Pressepraxis Gruppe 1','Basics in Press Practices','Einfhrung in die (pressebasierte)Redaktionsarbeit und in den praktischen Journalismus, unter besonderer Bercksichtigung moderner journalistischer Erzhlformen und konvergenter Arbeitsweisen im redaktionellen Alltag','6640-0008','deutsch','Spillmann M.',NULL,'Bachelor',2,3.0,'Studierende kennen das Berufsbild des Journalisten und verstehen dessen Arbeitsweise in einer modernen (pressebasierten) Redaktion, die Logik der Konvergenz moderner Medienbetriebe, deren Strukturen und Organisationsformen sowie die einschlgigen journalistischen Erzhlformen, Qualittsstandards und Marktgesetze','in der Veranstaltung','jedes Jahr','Tag Zeit Kurs / Übung Frequenz Raum Dienstag 13:15 - 15:00 Kurs wöchentlich PER 21 E230','Keine Einschränkung','zugelassen',NULL,'zugelassen','-','Reglement vom 19. Mai 2014 der Examina an der Wirtschafts- und Sozialwissenschaftlichen Fakultt der Universitt Freiburg','Winter 17; Wiederholung 17','2017-01-10 17:00:00','schriftliche PrüfungDie Prfungseinschreibung Wintersession 2017 findet vom 15. September 09:00 bis 14. Oktober 2016 12:00 auf mySES statt.Die Prfungseinschreibung Wiederholungssession 2017 findet vom 24. Juli bis 4. August 2017 12:00 auf mySES statt.	Ohne Einschreibung in der genannten Frist knnen keine Prfungen in der gewhlten Session abgelegt werden. Bitte merken Sie sich den Termin unbedingt vor.','60 Min','deutsch','Zählt für die folgenden Programme: Kommunikationswissenschaft und Medienforschung - zweites / drittes Jahr Kommunikationswissenschaft und Medienforschung: Bachelornebenfach (60 ECTS)','2017-05-06 13:27:17.646864','2017-05-06 13:27:17.646864');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 16 (Semester Course)','Monetary theory and policy I: The theory of monetary policy',NULL,'Ce cours a pour objectif dtudier les bases thoriques de la politique montaire. Il comporte trois parties. La premire porte sur les objectifs et les instruments de la politique montaire. La deuxime est consacre aux problmes lis au contrle de loffre de monnaie. La troisime analyse le choix entre rgles et pragmatisme afin daccrotre la transparence et la crdibilit des autorits montaires. Les cours sont complts par des sminaires (tous les 15 jours).','6610-0287','English','Rossi S.','Massonnet J.  Email : jonathan.massonnet@unifr.ch','Master',3,4.5,'This course aims at providing students with the body of knowledge required to understand the theoretical foundations of current monetary policy.','Rossi, S. (2008) Macroconomie montaire: thories et politiques, Brussels, Paris and Zrich: Bruylant, LGDJ and Schulthess.','every 2 years','Day Hour Course / Excercise Frequency Room Friday 8:15 - 11:00 Course weekly PER 21 B130','No restriction','Not authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  17; Re-assessment 17',NULL,'oral exam: AucunThe registration period winter period 2017 for the exam will be from September 15th 09:00 to October 14th 2016 12:00 am on mySES.The examinations registration period for the re-assessment period 2017 will be open on mySES from 24th July to 4th August 2017, 12:00 am.	Without registration in the given period, no exam in the choosen period can be taken. Please take note of the deadline.','15 Min','French; German; English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; Module 2: Economic Policy Master in Economics; Module 3: Economic Sustainability and Development Master in Economics; Module 7: Economic Theory Master in Economics; Offer Master list Economics Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.650204','2017-05-06 13:27:17.650204');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SA 16 (cours semestriel)','Microéconomie I','Intermediate Microeconomics I','Consommation et production:Le cours porte sur les principaux facteurs de la consommation et de la production,  savoir la demande, l''offre, les interactions entre la demande et l''offre, les lasticits, la thorie du consommateur et la thorie du producteur (cots de production). Le cours est complt par des sances d''exercices ainsi que par des prsentations thmatiques qui portent sur des applications concrtes des donnes thoriques, notamment dans le domaine de la concurrence.','SEEP02A001','français','Gugler P.','Resbeut M.  email : mathieu.resbeut@unifr.ch','Bachelor',4,6.0,'Matrise des principaux facteurs de la consommation et de la production,  savoir la demande, l''offre, les interactions entre la demande et l''offre, les lasticits, la thorie du consommateur et la thorie du producteur (cots de production).','1. N. Gregory Mankiw et P. Mark Taylor, Principes de l''Economie (adaptation europenne), 4me dition, Bruxelles: De Boeck, 2015. (version anglaise galement disponible)2. Robert S. Pindyck et Daniel L. Rubinfeld, Microconomie, 8me dition, Pearson Education, 2012. (version anglaise galement disponible)','chaque anne','Date Heure Cours / Excercice Salle Vendredi 23.09.2016 8:15 - 12:00 Cours PER 22 002 Vendredi 30.09.2016 8:15 - 12:00 Cours PER 22 002 Vendredi 07.10.2016 8:15 - 12:00 Cours PER 22 002 Vendredi 14.10.2016 8:15 - 12:00 Cours PER 22 002 Vendredi 21.10.2016 8:15 - 12:00 Cours PER 22 002 Vendredi 28.10.2016 8:15 - 12:00 Cours PER 22 002 Vendredi 04.11.2016 8:15 - 12:00 Cours PER 22 002 Vendredi 11.11.2016 8:15 - 12:00 Cours PER 22 002 Vendredi 18.11.2016 8:15 - 12:00 Cours PER 22 002 Vendredi 25.11.2016 13:15 - 17:00 Cours PER 22 002 Vendredi 02.12.2016 13:15 - 17:00 Cours PER 22 002 Vendredi 09.12.2016 8:15 - 12:00 Cours PER 22 002 Vendredi 16.12.2016 8:15 - 12:00 Cours PER 22 002 Vendredi 23.12.2016 8:15 - 12:00 Cours PER 22 002','Pas de restri