INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 16 (Semester Course)','Lecture Strategic communication Campaigns in a Global Society',NULL,'To be successful in todays competitive marketplace, communication professionals must understand diverse stakeholders and create culturally relevant campaigns to engage them. This course examines strategic communication campaigns in a contemporary, digital, and global society. Students gain understanding of theory and research for strategic planning, best practices in global communication management, and the growing influence of consumers and employees empowered by social and mobile media. Multicultural and multinational cases are examined. Topics include activism, crisis management, corporate social responsibility, health promotion, environmental sustainability, public diplomacy and nation building, product promotion and branding, community engagement, entertainment, sports, and popular culture. Students will gain understanding of the importance of technology, globalization, and ethics, and the power of strategic communication to influence society and motivate change.','6640-1642','English','Werder K.',NULL,'Bachelor',2,3.0,' To build a foundation of knowledge in strategic communication management; To develop the ability to apply a variety of theoretical perspectives to analyze and understand strategic communication campaigns; To develop the ability to strategically manage the communication function in various organizations; To develop the ability to use of new technologies and media in strategic communication; To develop an understanidng of how research informs communication campaign management,  To improve critical thinking and problem solving abilities;  To improve verbal and nonverbal communication skills.',NULL,'-','Day Hour Course / Excercise Frequency Room Monday 13:15 - 15:00 Course weekly PER 21 G230','No restriction','Authorised','t','Erasmus students are not admitted to courses / seminaries with limited number of participants, unless exception granted by the professor at the request of the student.','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'Continuous evaluationThe registration period on mySES for this seminar will be from September 15th 09:00 to October 14th 2016 12:00 am. The registration for this seminar also implies the registration to the assessment period.After October 14th 2016 12:00 am, you cannot register any more to the seminar nor withdraw from the course / seminarThe seminar registration  also implies also the registration for the seminar paper.',NULL,'English','Valid for the following programmes: Communication and Media Research: Major (120 ECTS); Wahlvorlesungen Kommunikationswissenschaft','2017-05-06 13:27:17.729665','2017-05-06 13:27:17.729665');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SA 16 (cours semestriel)','Informatique de gestion I','Fundamentals of Information Systems I','Ce cours comporte trois lments: (1) une brve introduction thorique au concept de systmes d''information; (2) une introduction thorique et pratique relativement approfondie aux bases de donnes relationnelles [1] et au langage SQL; (3) des exercices sur machine pour mettre en pratique les concepts enseigns.','SEIG02A002','français','Pasquier-Rocha J.','Aebischer N.  email : nadia.aebischer@unifr.ch','Bachelor',4,6.0,'- Savoir modliser des systmes d''information (bonne comprhension du modle entit-relation et des bases de donnes relationnelles).- Bnficier d''une solide connaissance de base du langage SQL.','[1] Meier A., trad. Nguyen D.H., Introduction pratique aux bases de donnes relationnelles, deuxime dition, Springer Verlag, France, 2006.[2] Un support de cours sera propos en dbut d''anne.[3] La plateforme Internet Moodle sera aussi utilise : forum de discussion, gestion des exercices, distribution de documents complmentaires, ...','chaque anne','Jour Heure Cours / Excercice Fréquence Salle Mardi 10:15 - 13:00 Cours hebdomadaire PER 21 A140 Mardi 13:15 - 15:00 Exercices hebdomadaire PER 21 F230 Mardi 15:15 - 17:00 Exercices hebdomadaire PER 21 F230','Pas de restrictions','Autorisés','t','Autorisés','-','Rglement du 19 mai 2014 sur l''organisation des tudes et des examens  la Facult des sciences conomiques et sociales de l''Universit de Fribourg','Hiver 17; Rattrapage 17','0001-03-17 08:30:00','épreuve écriteL''inscription  l''preuve de la session d''hiver 2017 a lieu du 15 septembre 9h00 au 14 octobre 2016 12h00 sur mySES.L'' inscription  l''preuve de la session de rattrapage 2017 a lieu du 24 juillet au 4 aot 2017 12h00 sur mySES.	Sans inscription dans le dlai cit ci-dessus, l''preuve ne peut pas tre passe dans la session choisi. Veuillez imprativement respecter le dlai d''inscription aux preuves.','90 minutes','français','Valable pour les programmes suivants: Bachelor en économie politique Bachelor en gestion d''entreprise Bachelor en informatique de gestion Informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (30 ECTS) Business Communication - informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.733869','2017-05-06 13:27:17.733869');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 16 (Semester Course)','International B2B-Marketing',NULL,'This course provides students with solid experience in creating market-driven and market-driving strategies for the future success of a business to business firm. A focus is on discovering and developing a set of unique competencies for a B2B firm that, through strategic differentiation, leads to sustainable competitive advantage in the marketplace. Students are provided ample opportunity to develop and practice creative problem-solving and decision-making skills to simulate the requirements of todays complex international B2B market environment.','6620-0564','English','Furrer O.','Boninsegni M.  Email : melanie.boninsegni@unifr.ch','Master',3,4.5,'This course takes a marketing leadership/Chief Marketing Office (CMO) perspective in order to enhance your ability to use B2B marketing in an international context to maximize firm performance.','Dwyer, F. Robert and Tanner, John F., Jr. (2009), Business Marketing: Connecting Strategy, Relationships, and Learning, 4th edition, McGraw-Hill: Boston.','every 2 years','Date Hour Course / Excercise Room Friday 23.09.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Seminar PER 21 G230 Friday 07.10.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Seminar PER 21 G230 Friday 14.10.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Seminar PER 21 G230 Friday 21.10.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Seminar PER 21 G230 Friday 28.10.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Seminar PER 21 G230 Friday 04.11.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Seminar PER 21 G230 Thursday 10.11.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Seminar PER 21 G120 Friday 18.11.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Seminar PER 21 G230 Friday 25.11.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Seminar PER 21 G230 Friday 02.12.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Seminar PER 21 G230 Friday 09.12.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Seminar PER 21 G230 Friday 16.12.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Seminar PER 21 G230 Friday 23.12.2016 13:15 - 16:00 Seminar PER 21 G230','No restriction','Not authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  17; Re-assessment 17',NULL,'Continuous evaluation + written examThe registration period on mySES for this course / seminar will be from September 15th 9h00  to October 14th 2016 12:00 am. After October 14th 2016 12:00 am, you cannot register any more to the exam or cancel this  exam.','90 min','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; Module 3: Marketing (MAR) Master in Management; Module 8: European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Module European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Module Marketing (MAR) Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.737653','2017-05-06 13:27:17.737653');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 16 (Semester Course)','International Finance',NULL,'Most companies and individuals conduct their business in an increasingly integrated world. Doing business in an international context raises different problems that are not encountered in a domestic setting. Therefore a sound understanding of the mechanics of international financial markets and of principles of international financial management should be part of the background of any modern manager. This course provides the necessary tools to face these challenges and also shows how the main concept of finance can be extended to an international environment. The course first describes the international financial environment. The second part analyzes portfolio investment decisions in such a context while the third part considers the main issues faced by the firm in an international environment as well as their solutions.','6620-0165','English','Isakov D.','Schwab D.  Email : dominic.schwab@unifr.ch','Master',3,4.5,'Understand and master the main tools and concepts of international finance','Bekaert G. and R. Hodrick, 2012, International Financial Management, Pearson Education.Butler K., 2016, Multinational Finance (6th edition), Wiley & Sons.Eiteman K., Stonehill A. and M. Moffett, 2016, Multinational Business Finance (14th edition), Pearson Addison Wesley.Eun C. and B. Resnick, 2014, International Financial Management, (7th edition), McGraw-Hill International.Solnik B. and D. McLeavey, 2009, International Investments (6th edition), Pearson Addison Wesley.Sercu P., 2009, International finance: Theory into practice, Princeton University Press.','every 2 years','Day Hour Course / Excercise Frequency Room Thursday 10:15 - 13:00 Course weekly PER 21 A140','No restriction','Not authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg','Winter  17; Re-assessment 17',NULL,'written exam: Calculator + 1 page of hand-written notesThe registration period winter period 2017 for the exam will be from September 15th 09:00 to October 14th 2016 12:00 am on mySES.The examinations registration period for the re-assessment period 2017 will be open on mySES from 24th July to 4th August 2017, 12:00 am.	Without registration in the given period, no exam in the choosen period can be taken. Please take note of the deadline.','90 minutes','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; Module 9: Finance Master in Economics; Module 9: Finance Master in Management; Module 4: Finance (FIN) Master in Management; Module 8: European Business (EUB) Master in Accounting and Finance; Module Finance (FIN) Master in European Business; Module European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Module Finance (FIN) Master in Informationsmanagement Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.743089','2017-05-06 13:27:17.743089');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'HS 16 (Semesterkurs)','Internationales Handelsmanagement',NULL,'Obwohl der Handel fr den erfolgreichen Absatz von Produkten unentbehrlich ist, befassen sich Studierende meist zu wenig mit dem Detailhandel, also dem Absatzkanal, der an private Konsumenten verkauft, als auch mit dem Grosshandel, der seine Produkte an  gewerbliche Kunden, z.B. Handwerker, Industriebetriebe oder den Detailhandel, vertreibt. Zwar ist hier der Online-Handel von aktuell hohem Interesse, aber auch der stationre Handel ist als zentrales Glied der Marketingkette auch fr Hersteller von grosser Bedeutung.Im Kurs werden unterschiedliche Betriebstypen beleuchtet, Entwicklungen im stationren und im Online-Handel diskutiert und Internationalisierungsstrategien betrachtet. Es werden unterschiedliche Unternehmensfunktionen (z.B. Handelsmarketing, Supply-Chain-Management) und unterschiedliche Fhrungsprozesse (z.B. Controlling) dargestellt. Auch die Kooperation von Handel und Herstellern entlang der Wertschpfungskette wird analysiert.Dabei wird sowohl der Detailhandel (Unternehmen wie z.B. Coop, Media-Markt, Zalando) als auch der Grosshandel (Unternehmen wie z.B. Wrth oder Prodega) betrachtet, da die unterschiedlichen Zielgruppen auch unterschiedliche Strategien und Anforderungen an das Management nach sich ziehen. Die bungen im Kurs werden in Form von Gruppenarbeiten und prsentationen durchgefhrt, um anhand von Fallstudien Handelsstrategien noch besser zu durchdringen.','6620-0592','deutsch','Morschett D.','Schmid D.  Email : david.schmid@unifr.ch','Master',3,4.5,'Die Studierenden sollen einen umfassenden Einblick in die Strategien und das Management von Detailhandels- und Grosshandelsunternehmen erhalten. Dabei sollen Kenntnisse sowohl ber den stationren Handel als auch ber den Online-Handel vermittelt werden.','Zentes, Joachim; Morschett, Dirk; Schramm-Klein, Hanna: Strategic Retail Management, 2nd ed.,(Gabler) Wiesbaden 2011.Zentes, Joachim; Swoboda, Bernhard; Foscht, Thomas: Handelsmanagement, 3. Aufl., (Vahlen) Mnchen 2012.Zustzlich werden Beitrge aus wissenschaftlichen Zeitschriften im Rahmen der Vorlesung zur Verfgung gestellt.','alle 2 Jahre','Tag Zeit Kurs / Übung Frequenz Raum Montag 14:15 - 16:00 Kurs wöchentlich PER 21 D130 Dienstag 10:15 - 12:00 Übungen ungerade Wochen PER 21 E120','Keine Einschränkung','Nicht zugelassen',NULL,'zugelassen','-','Reglement vom 19. Mai 2014 der Examina an der Wirtschafts- und Sozialwissenschaftlichen Fakultt der Universitt Freiburg','Winter 17; Wiederholung 17','2017-01-23 11:00:00','Fortlaufende Evaluation + schriftliche Prüfung: Erstellung einer Gruppenarbeit (und -prsentation) im Laufe der Vorlesung bzw. bung (40% der Gesamtnote) plus schriftliches Examen (60% der Gesamtnote). Beide Teile mssen separat mit mindestens einer 4.0 bestanden werden, damit der Kurs insgesamt als bestanden gilt.Die Einschreibung fr diesen Kurs / Seminar ist auf mySES in der Zeit vom 15. September 9h00  14. Oktober 2016 12:00Nach dem 14. Oktober 2016 12:00 knnen Sie sich nicht mehr fr diese Prfung  einschreiben oder  von dieser Prfung  zurckziehen.','60 Min','deutsch','Zählt für die folgenden Programme: Master in Betriebswirtschaftslehre; Wahlmodul 1: Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Betriebswirtschaftslehre; Wahlmodul 3: Marketing (MAR) Master in Betriebswirtschaftslehre; Wahlmodul 8: European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Modul European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Modul Marketing (MAR) Master in European Business; Modul Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Wirtschaftsinformatik Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.746046','2017-05-06 13:27:17.746046');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SA 16 (cours semestriel)','Méthodes empiriques des sciences sociales','Méthodes empiriques des sciences sociales','Introduction aux mthodes empiriques des sciences sociales avec prsentation thorique et pratique des diffrentes tapes du processus de recherche, de la rcolte des donnes aux phases d''analyse. Le cours aborde en particulier le design de la recherche, les diffrents modes de collecte des donnes ( questionnaire, entretien, observation...) et les diffrentes mthodes d''analyse.','6640-1494','français','Cauhp F.',NULL,'Bachelor',3,4.5,'Acqurir des connaissances thoriques, mthodologiques et pratiques sur les processus de recherche propres aux mthodes empiriques en sciences sociales. Les tudiants auront un aperu des diverses faons de rcolter des donnes de qualit, puis de les traiter. Les tudiants seront capables d''viter les erreurs typiques dans la conduite d''un projet de recherche en sciences sociales.','- Manuel de recherche en sciences sociales, Luc Van Campenhoudt, Raymond Quivy, Dunod, 4me dition, 2011- Mthodes des sciences sociales, Madeleine Grawitz, Prcis Dalloz,11me d. 2001- Mthodologie de la recherche en sciences de gestion, M-L Gavard-Perret, D. Gatteland, Ch. Haon, A. Jolibert, Pearson, 2me d.2012','chaque anne','Jour Heure Cours / Excercice Fréquence Salle Mercredi 9:15 - 12:00 Cours hebdomadaire PER 21 C140','Pas de restrictions','Autorisés','t','Autorisés','-','Rglement du 19 mai 2014 sur l''organisation des tudes et des examens  la Facult des sciences conomiques et sociales de l''Universit de Fribourg','Hiver 17; Rattrapage 17','2017-01-11 08:30:00','épreuve écriteL''inscription  l''preuve de la session d''hiver 2017 a lieu du 15 septembre 9h00 au 14 octobre 2016 12h00 sur mySES.L'' inscription  l''preuve de la session de rattrapage 2017 a lieu du 24 juillet au 4 aot 2017 12h00 sur mySES.	Sans inscription dans le dlai cit ci-dessus, l''preuve ne peut pas tre passe dans la session choisi. Veuillez imprativement 