INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 17 (Semester Course)','Business Negotiation',NULL,'The course combines lectures by the instructor and practical exercises. It is essential for students to be actively involved in exercises, games and negotiation simulations. Students should carefully read the instructions, and fill out the assigned outcomes sheets for each game and simulation. Systematic debriefing of negotiation exercises, games and simulations brings important insights and should be considered a full part of the content of the course, beyond mere illustration of key points presented during lectures.','6620-0572','English','Usunier J.-C.','Boninsegni M.  Email : melanie.boninsegni@unifr.ch','Master',3,4.5,'Students should acquire through this course basic theoretical knowledge on negotiation with a clear focus on business negotiation (sales negotiation, social negotiation, business agreements, mergers and acquisitions, intra-organizational negotiation, etc.). Students should also acquire a sense of practical aspects of negotiation as well as increase their skills through a number of negotiation exercises and simulations which enable them to develop ownership of negotiation knowledge and put it into practical perspective.','Ghauri, Pervez N. et Jean-Claude Usunier (2003), International Business Negotiations, second edition, Pergamon/Elsevier: Oxford.A set of additional references is given at the end of the course outline.','each year',NULL,'50','Not authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'Continuous evaluation + written exam: - 50 % class assignments - 50 % final exam (it will deal with all what was presented during lectures + assigned readings + debriefings of the negotiations exercises, games, and simulations + text in this document). No document is allowed during the 1 hour written exam. Questions cover the whole course content.','60 minutes','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; GMT: General Management Master in Management; MAR: Marketing Master in Management; Module 1: Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Management; Module 2: Organization and Human Resource Management (OHR) Master in Management; Module 3: Marketing (MAR) Master in Management; OHRM: Organisation and Human Resource Management Master in Management; STR: Strategy Master in European Business; GMT: General Management Master in European Business; MAR: Marketing Master in European Business; Module Marketing (MAR) Master in European Business; Module Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in European Business; STR: Strategy Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.803204','2017-05-06 13:27:17.803204');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'HS 17 (Semesterkurs)','Das Freiburger Management-Modell','The Fribourg management approach (FMM) for NPO','Das Management von Nonprofit-Organisationen (NPO) wie Wirtschafts- und Arbeitnehmerverbnde, Genossenschaften, Vereine, Parteien, soziale Dienstleistungsunternehmen (Einrichtungen, Heime, Beratungsdienste) sowie philanthropische, kulturelle und Freizeit-Organisationen unterscheidet sich wesentlich vom Management profitorientierter Unternehmen. Nicht nur die Orientierung an einem spezifischen Sachziel, sondern auch die basisorientierte Steuerung, die Fhrung durch Milizgremien, die Vielfalt der Aussenbeziehungen, das Erstellen von Kollektivleistungen, das Wahrnehmen von Lobbyingaufgaben usw. stellen Fhrungskrfte vor ganz besondere Aufgaben. Das Freiburger Management-Modell fr NPO bietet eine systematische Einfhrung in die Thematik. Durch den ganzheitlichen Ansatz bildet es die Grundlage und ein Ordnungsraster fr das Verstndnis der Management-Probleme von NPO und deren Lsungsanstze.','6620-0310','deutsch','Lichtsteiner H.','Aeschbacher R.  Email : remo.aeschbacher@unifr.ch','Master',2,3.0,'Die Teilnehmenden kennen die Besonderheiten des Managements von Nonprofit-Organisationen, knnen ihr Managementwissen an diese besonderen Bedrfnisse anpassen, dies unter Wahrung des Gesamtkontexts des systemischen Ansatzes des Freiburger Management-Modells fr NPO.','Lichtsteiner/Gmr/Giroud/Schauer: Das Freiburger Management-Modell fr Nonprofit-Organisationen, 8. Aufl., Bern/Stuttgart/Wien: Haupt Verlag, 2015','jedes Jahr',NULL,'Keine Einschränkung','Nicht zugelassen',NULL,'Erasmusstudierende sind zu Kursen / Seminaren mit beschrnkter Teilnehmerzahl nicht zugelassen, ausser der Dozent gewhrt dem Studierenden auf Antrag eine Ausnahme.','-','Reglement vom 19. Mai 2014 der Examina an der Wirtschafts- und Sozialwissenschaftlichen Fakultt der Universitt Freiburg',NULL,NULL,'schriftliche Prüfung: Sur demande l''examen peut tre en langue franaise.','60 Minuten','französisch; deutsch','Zählt für die folgenden Programme: Master in Betriebswirtschaftslehre; NPO: Nonprofit Management Master in Betriebswirtschaftslehre; Wahlmodul 7: Public and Nonprofit Management (NPO) Master in Wirtschaftsinformatik Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.806075','2017-05-06 13:27:17.806075');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 17 (Semester Course)','Case studies in international strategy',NULL,'Course content:● Introduction to internationalization and international strategy ● Process for developing a growth strategy for a region● Example of a group presentation of a former year● Briefings● Group work on real cases in international strategy● Group presentations and discussions on real cases in international strategyProgram:● Introduction on Wednesday, 27.09.2017● Block course on Friday, 29.09.2017● Briefing by the company on Friday, 06.10.2017● First discussion of the groups with the lecturer on Friday, 17.11.2017● Second discussion of the groups with the lecturer on Thursday, 30.11.2017● Group presentations on Thursday, 14.12.2017There will be 3 working groups of 4 students','6620-0554','English','Grnig R.','Blanc A.  Email : amandine.blanc@unifr.ch','Master',3,4.5,'General objective:To be able to systematically approach an issue in international strategy and to produce a clear solutionSubgoals:● To have an overview of international strategy● To know important methodological approaches and to be able to apply them in a real case● To get the needed information through company documents, interviews and internet research● To carry out a strategic analysis and to propose a solution to a real issue● To present and justify analysis and proposition','● Outline● Grnig, R., Morschett, D. (2017): Developing International Strategies, Second edition, Springer Berlin and Heidelberg● 2 handouts● Example of a group presentation of a former year','each year',NULL,'12','Not authorised','t','Erasmus students are not admitted to courses / seminaries with limited number of participants, unless exception granted by the professor at the request of the student.','Conditions:● Compulsory attendance during all the seminar dates● Possibility to meet the other students to elaborate a solution for the caseSelection criteria:1. Performance of the student2. Advancement in the studyApplication on mySESApplication period: 14.09.17-24.09.17','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'oral exam: 50%group presentation: 50%','15 Min.','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; Module 8: Industrial Organization Master in Management; EUGB: European and Global Business Master in Management; Module 1: Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in Management; Module 8: European Business (EUB) Master in Management; STR: Strategy Master in European Business; EUGB: European and Global Business Master in European Business; Module European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Module Strategic and General Management (STM) Master in European Business; STR: Strategy Master in Informationsmanagement Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.808803','2017-05-06 13:27:17.808803');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SA 17 (cours semestriel)','Colloque/Kolloquium','Research Seminar for Graduates','Les projets de recherche sont prsents et discuts dans le colloque, notamment en ce qui concerne les aspects mthodologiques.','6640-0196','français','Bourgeois D. / Asdourian B.',NULL,'Master',0,3.0,'Important : il n''y a pas d''inscription sur MySES a effectuer. L''tudiant-e vient directement aux sances qu''il/elle dsire (nous conseillons la venue pour la premire sance).Le colloque a pour but de favoriser lapprofondissement dun projet de recherche visant  dboucher sur un mmoire de Master ou un Doctorat.',NULL,'chaque anne',NULL,'12','Pas autorisés','t','Etudiants Erasmus pas admis au cours / sminaires avec un nombre limit de participants, sauf si exception accorde par le professeur sur demande de ltudiant.','-','Rglement du 19 mai 2014 sur l''organisation des tudes et des examens  la Facult des sciences conomiques et sociales de l''Universit de Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'Evaluation continue',NULL,'français','Valable pour les programmes suivants: Master in Business Communication','2017-05-06 13:27:17.811501','2017-05-06 13:27:17.811501');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SA 17 (cours semestriel)','Droit I','Business Law I','Aprs quelques notions gnrales sur lordre juridique (Introduction gnrale), le but du cours consistera  prsenter :	dans une premire partie, une introduction au droit public conomique applicable en Suisse,  savoir, en particulier, la constitution conomique, quelques lois de droit public conomique et, enfin, les rgles de droit public conomique relevant de lordre juridique international ; une brve introduction au droit suisse des socits sera encore propose en fin de premire partie;	dans une seconde partie, une introduction au droit priv, dans laquelle on sattachera  dterminer quels sont les acteurs, lobjet et les instruments de la vie conomique suisse au regard de lordre juridique ; y seront galement abordes les questions lies aux relations de droit priv avec ltranger, ainsi que celles lies aux procdures permettant lapplication du droit priv et  lexcution force des obligations.','SEGE02A007','français','Dubey B. / Brahier J.-M.',NULL,'Bachelor',3,4.5,'Connaissances gnrales de base en droit des personnes, en droit constitutionnel et en droit public conomique suisse; capacit de rsoudre des petits cas dans ces domaines.',NULL,'chaque anne',NULL,'Pas de restrictions','Autorisés','t','Autorisés','-','Rglement du 19 mai 2014 sur l''organisation des tudes et des examens  la Facult des sciences conomiques et sociales de l''Universit de Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'épreuve écrite','90 minutes','français','Valable pour les programmes suivants: Bachelor en économie politique Bachelor en gestion d''entreprise Bachelor en informatique de gestion Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.814757','2017-05-06 13:27:17.814757');
