INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SA 17 (cours semestriel)','Communication I: Théories de la communication et des médias','Mass Communication  Research  Introductory Course','Le cours expose quelques thories de la communication et de l''influence des mdias.Seront notamment tudies, les notions telles que : o La communication interpersonnelle, avec notamment :- le schma de la communication - Moles ;- la thorie mathmatique de la communication - Shannon et Weaver ;- la cyberntique de Wiener ;- la logique de communication - Watzlawick- l''engagement et la soumission librement consentie - Lewin & Kiesler & Joul & Beauvois & Bernard ;- la face des individus : perte/conservation/rtablissement - Goffman.o La communication de masse, avec notamment :- la seringue hypodermique - Lasswell ;   - le viol des foules par la propagande - Tchakhotine ;- les 5 W - Lasswell ;- les leaders d''opinions - Lazarsfeld & Katz ;- le rle du journaliste - Westley et Mc Lean ;- l''effet d''endormissement - Hovland :- l''approche fonctionnaliste des mdias - Wright ;- l''cole critique de Francfort - Habermas ;- la fonction d''agenda - Mc Combs & Shaw ;- la spirale du silence - Noelle-Neumann.o la communication par les signes, avec notamment :- la linguistique - de Saussure ;- les fonctions du langage - Jakobson ;- la smiologie - Peirce ;- la rhtorique de l''image - Barthes.','6640-0004','français','Asdourian B.',NULL,'Bachelor',2,3.0,'Prsenter les principales thories de la communication et des mdias','J. Lohisse : La communication. De la transmission  la relation, De Boeck.Mige B., La pense communicationnelle, Presse Universitaire de Grenoble.D''autres rfrences seront transmises en cours.','chaque anne',NULL,'Pas de restrictions','Autorisés','t','Autorisés','-','Rglement du 19 mai 2014 sur l''organisation des tudes et des examens  la Facult des sciences conomiques et sociales de l''Universit de Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'épreuve écrite','60 Min','français','Valable pour les programmes suivants: Bachelor en économie politique Bachelor en gestion d''entreprise Kommunikationswissenschaft und Medienforschung - erstes Jahr Préalable au Master in Business Communication Kommunikationswissenschaft und Medienforschung: Bachelornebenfach (60 ECTS) Kommunikationswissenschaft und Medienforschung: Bachelornebenfach (30 ECTS) Communication et médias: branche complémentaire Bachelor (30 ECTS) Business Communication - économie politique: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Business Communication - gestion d''entreprise: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Business Communication - informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Business Communication - informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) pr BSc INF','2017-05-06 13:27:17.819913','2017-05-06 13:27:17.819913');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 17 (Semester Course)','Business and Human Rights',NULL,'The course seeks to provide a solid grounding in business and human rights as an emerging and rapidly developing field. Students should be able to apply key concepts learned to practical, real-life examples, and to understand current and evolving debates around corporate responsibility to respect human rights. The first part of the course introduces the field of business and human rights (why human rights matter to business; the state of the international debate on corporate responsibility to respect human rights; the evolution of the UN framework and Guiding Principles on business and human rights) and presents an overview of measures and mechanisms through which stakeholders might hold business accountable for this responsibility (legal mechanisms; multi-stakeholder initiatives; civil society organization campaigns; shareholder activism; corporate reporting; emerging international standards). The second part takes a more sectoral/thematic approach, focusing on several areas that pose particularly difficult human rights challenges for companies (extractive industries; supply chain labor standards; operating in conflict areas), examining key issues in these areas and exploring how companies, civil society organizations, governments and other stakeholders have sought to address these. The course concludes with a brief survey of emerging topics in business and human rights as well as potential new business models (e.g. benefit corporations) and their implications for corporate responsibility to respect human rights.','6610-0501','English','Umlas E.',NULL,'Master',2,3.0,'Provide a solid grounding in the emerging field of business and human rights, and enable students to apply key concepts learned to practical, real-life examples of companies and their stakeholders facing challenges in this area',NULL,'each year',NULL,'No restriction','Not authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'Continuous evaluation + oral exam: Les notes finales seront bases sur une preuve orale mais qui tient compte aussi dans une petite mesure d''autres lments. Pour tre autoris  passer l''examen, les tudiants doivent assister  au moins 4 des 7 sessions de ce cours. Final grades will be based on an oral exam but a small percentage of the final grade will be based on other elements. To be permitted to take the final exam, students must attend at least 4 out of the 7 sessions of this course.','15 Min','French; English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; Module 4: Business Ethics and Social Responsibility Master in Economics; Offer Master list Economics Master in Management; GMT: General Management Master in Management; OHRM: Organisation and Human Resource Management Master in European Business; GMT: General Management Ethics and Economics: 30 ECTS Minor Master; Module I : thique et droits humains Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.824159','2017-05-06 13:27:17.824159');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 17 (Semester Course)','Customer orientation and complaint management',NULL,'The course consists of several components:- theoretical component: discussion of theoretical approaches in the fields of customer satisfaction, complaint management, customer retention, and CRM- analytical component: showing the application of quantitative methods (e.g., regression analysis, ANOVA) in order to develop strategies in the field of customer satisfaction and retention - practical component: compiling the major issues of a professional complaint management on the basis of real examples from marketing practice (group work and presentation)- scientific component: going through selected scientific articles in the field of satisfaction, complaint and retention researchThe group work projects are a mandatory part of the course. The overall exam grade will be calculated as follows: 0.15* grade of the group work project + 0.85*grade of the written exam.','6620-0534','English','Bambauer-Sachse S.','Massera L.  Email : laura.massera@unifr.ch','Master',3,4.5,'The purpose of this course is to discuss theoretical aspects of customer orientation and complaint management, to show the major issues of a professional complaint management through case study work and to explain how strategies can be developed on the basis of data analyses.','Kotler/Armstrong (2007): Principles of MarketingSolomon/Marshall/Stuart (2006): MarketingHomburg/Kuester/Krohmer (2009): Marketing ManagementDoole/Lancaster/Lowe (2005): Understanding and Managing CustomersBruhn (2003): Relationship MarketingEgan (2008): Relationship Marketing','every 2 years',NULL,'No restriction','Not authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'written exam','60 Min','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; MAR: Marketing Master in Management; Module 3: Marketing (MAR) Master in European Business; MAR: Marketing Master in European Business; Module Marketing (MAR) Master in Informationsmanagement Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.826989','2017-05-06 13:27:17.826989');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'HS 17 (Semesterkurs)','BWL II: Marketingkommunikation','Corporate Communications','Gegenstand dieses Kurses ist es, zentrale Begriffe, Grundlagen, Aufgaben, Ziele und Zielgruppen der Unternehmenskommunikation anzusprechen. Darber hinaus sollen verschiedene Kommunikationsinstrumente und Kommunikationsstrategien vorgestellt, die Mediaplanung besprochen und Grundlagen der Werbewirkung erlutert werden. Ziel des Kurses ist es, die Studierenden mit den zentralen Aspekten der Unternehmenskommunikation vertraut zu machen und ihnen rechnerische und analytische Problemlsungsfhigkeiten im Bereich der Unternehmenskommunikation zu vermitteln.','SEGE02A047','deutsch','Bambauer-Sachse S.',NULL,'Bachelor',3,4.5,'Das Ziel dieses Kurses ist es, einen berblick ber die verschiedenen Bereiche der Unternehmenskommunikation zu geben und die zentralen Aspekte der Unternehmenskommunikation aufzuzeigen.','Bruhn: KommunikationspolitikHomburg/Krohmer: MarketingmanagementNieschlag/Dichtl/Hrschgen: Marketing','jedes Jahr',NULL,'Keine Einschränkung','zugelassen',NULL,'zugelassen','-','Reglement vom 19. Mai 2014 der Examina an der Wirtschafts- und Sozialwissenschaftlichen Fakultt der Universitt Freiburg',NULL,NULL,'schriftliche Prüfung: nicht programmierbarer Taschenrechner ist zugelassen','60 Min','deutsch','Zählt für die folgenden Programme: Bachelor in Betriebswirtschaftslehre Management und Ökonomie: Hauptfach (120 ECTS); Wahlkurse in Betriebswirtschaftslehre Master in Betriebswirtschaftslehre; MAR: Marketing Master in Betriebswirtschaftslehre; Wahlmodul 3: Marketing (MAR) Master in European Business; MAR: Marketing Master in European Business; Modul Marketing (MAR) Betriebswirtschaftslehre: Bachelornebenfach (60 ECTS) Betriebswirtschaftslehre: Bachelornebenfach (30 ECTS) Business Communication - Betriebswirtschaftslehre: Bachelornebenfach (60 ECTS) Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.829561','2017-05-06 13:27:17.829561');
