INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SA 17 (cours semestriel)','Cours: Communication, organisation et e-Business','Course: Communication, organization and e-Business','Ce cours traite des volutions de la communication et des organisations lies au dveloppement des technologies de linformation et de la communication, et notamment dInternet. On rappellera les fondements thoriques permettant de cerner ces volutions et on examinera les nouvelles formes de mdiation qui se dveloppent avec les e-activits. Laccent sera mis sur les changements organisationnels et communicationnels dans le cadre du e-business. Les questions lies au e-marketing et  la cybercrise seront galement tudies.  This lecture analyses changes in communication and organizations related to the development of information and communication technology, more specifically Internet. Theoretical backgrounds which permit to understand these changes will be presented; then new forms of mediation which are developing with e-activities will be examined. We will insist on organizational and communicational changes in the framework of e-business. Questions related to e-marketing and cyber crisis will also be studied.','6640-1273','français','Bourgeois D.',NULL,'Master',2,3.0,'Objectifs du cours : ce cours a pour objectif de prsenter les grandes caractristiques des changements communicationnels et organisationnels, notamment lis  lessor dInternet et du e-business. Objectives of the course: this lecture aims at showing the main characteristics of the communicational and organizational changes, particularly linked to the development of Internet and e-business.','OuvragesArmstrong, G. & Kotler, P. (2016). Principes de marketing. Paris : Pearson Education. Badillo, P.-Y., & et Roux, D. (2009). Les 100 mots des tlcommunications. Paris : PUF. Balle, F. (2013). Mdias et socits. Paris : LGDJ. Balagu, C., & Fayon, D. (2012). Facebook, Twitter et les autres : Intgrer les rseaux sociaux dans une stratgie dentreprise. Paris : Pearson. Kotler, P., Keller, K., & Manceau, D. (2015). Marketing management. Montreuil : Pearson. Malaval ,P. & Dcaudin, J.-M. (2016). Pentacom. Montreuil : Pearson. Faur, B. & Arnaud, N. (2014). La communication des organisations. Paris : La Dcouverte. Libaert, T. (2015). La communication de crise. Paris : Dunod.Articles dans une revue scientifique Badillo, P.-Y., Bourgeois, D., & Asdourian, B., (2010). Les nouveaux champs de la communication des organisations  lments  partir du projet europen Fire Paradox. Les Cahiers du Numrique, 6(4), 167-180. En ligne : http://dominiquebourgeois.eu/2015/09/publications-en-ligne/ Coombs, W. T. (2007). Protecting organization reputations during a crisis: The development and application of situational crisis communication theory. Corporate reputation review, 10(3), 163-176. En ligne : http://www.johnstockmyer.com/enmu/ResearchArticle1.pdfChapitre douvrage Badillo, P.-Y., & Bourgeois D., (2013). Management de linformation et vanescence de la communication-relation dans les organisations ? Pour une thorie communicationnelle de lorganisation. In S. P. Alemanno et B. Parent (Dir.), Les communications organisationnelles, Comprendre, construire, observer (pp. 215-228). Paris : LHarmattan. En ligne http://dominiquebourgeois.eu/2015/09/publications-en-ligne/Voir la bibliographie plus complte donne dans le document de prsentation du cours.','chaque anne',NULL,'25','Pas autorisés','t','Etudiants Erasmus pas admis au cours / sminaires avec un nombre limit de participants, sauf si exception accorde par le professeur sur demande de ltudiant.','Inscription en ligne obligatoire. Tous les tudiants en Master Business Communication et pr-master Business Communication seront inscrits prioritairement. Les autres tudiants seront mis en liste d''attente et ventuellement inscrits, par la suite, en fonction des places disponibles.','Rglement du 19 mai 2014 sur l''organisation des tudes et des examens  la Facult des sciences conomiques et sociales de l''Universit de Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'Evaluation continue + épreuve écrite','60 Min','français','Valable pour les programmes suivants: Master en gestion dentreprise; MAR: Marketing Master en gestion dentreprise; Module 3: Marketing (MAR) Master en gestion dentreprise; Module 6: Information and Communication Technology (ICT) Master in European Business; MAR: Marketing Master in European Business; Modul Marketing (MAR) Master en informatique de gestion; ICT: Information and Communication Technology Master en Sciences de la Communication et Recherche sur les Médias; Modul B «Journalism and Organizational Communication» Master en Sciences de la Communication et Recherche sur les Médias; V. Organisationskommunikation und Public Relations Master in Business Communication','2017-05-06 13:27:17.854441','2017-05-06 13:27:17.854441');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 17 (Semester Course)','European Marketing',NULL,'In this course we will first examine the relevance of European Marketing as well as the market situation in the different countries. Trends towards homogeneity versus remaining heterogeneity are considered. The three broad areas of European marketing that are looked into are: market selection, market entry strategies, and marketing strategies/marketing mix. First, market selection criteria of international companies are explained, including the selection procedure. Second, the different options for the market entry, e.g. acquisition, franchising, joint ventures, are discussed and their advantages and disadvantages investigated. Thirdly, the different elements of the marketing strategy and the marketing mix (i.e. product policy, pricing policy, distribution policy and promotion/communication policy) are discussed in detail.Emphasis is given to the interdependence of these three main areas of European Marketing and to the differences between different industry sectors.','6620-0305','English','Morschett D.','Schmid D.  Email : david.schmid@unifr.ch','Master',3,4.5,'The course is designed to introduce students to the particularities of international marketing in European markets.','Hollensen, Svend: Global Marketing, 6th edition, FT Prentice Hall, 2014.	The required readings will also include a number of articles from journals. These will be provided by the chair.','every 2 years',NULL,'No restriction','Not authorised','t','Authorised','The requirements for the Master of Arts in European Business are listed in detail in the regulations (reglement). Previous knowledge of the subject is not required. However, basic knowledge of marketing is very beneficial.','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'written exam','60 Min','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; EUGB: European and Global Business Master in Management; MAR: Marketing Master in Management; Module 3: Marketing (MAR) Master in Management; Module 8: European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; EUGB: European and Global Business Master in European Business; MAR: Marketing Master in European Business; Module European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; Module Marketing (MAR) Master in Informationsmanagement Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:17.858431','2017-05-06 13:27:17.858431');
