INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SA 17 (cours semestriel)','Méthodes empiriques des sciences sociales','Méthodes empiriques des sciences sociales','Introduction aux mthodes empiriques des sciences sociales avec prsentation thorique et pratique des diffrentes tapes du processus de recherche, de la rcolte des donnes aux phases d''analyse. Le cours aborde en particulier le design de la recherche, les diffrents modes de collecte des donnes ( questionnaire, entretien, observation...) et les diffrentes mthodes d''analyse.','6640-1494','français','Cauhp F.',NULL,'Bachelor',3,4.5,'Acqurir des connaissances thoriques, mthodologiques et pratiques sur les processus de recherche propres aux mthodes empiriques en sciences sociales. Les tudiants auront un aperu des diverses faons de rcolter des donnes de qualit, puis de les traiter. Les tudiants seront capables d''viter les erreurs typiques dans la conduite d''un projet de recherche en sciences sociales.','- Manuel de recherche en sciences sociales, Luc Van Campenhoudt, Raymond Quivy, Dunod, 4me dition, 2011- Mthodes des sciences sociales, Madeleine Grawitz, Prcis Dalloz,11me d. 2001- Mthodologie de la recherche en sciences de gestion, M-L Gavard-Perret, D. Gatteland, Ch. Haon, A. Jolibert, Pearson, 2me d.2012','chaque anne',NULL,'Pas de restrictions','Autorisés','t','Autorisés','-','Rglement du 19 mai 2014 sur l''organisation des tudes et des examens  la Facult des sciences conomiques et sociales de l''Universit de Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'épreuve écrite','60','français','Valable pour les programmes suivants: Bachelor en économie politique Bachelor en gestion d''entreprise Bachelor en informatique de gestion Kommunikationswissenschaft und Medienforschung - erstes Jahr Gestion d''entreprise: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Préalable au Master in Business Communication Complément au Master en gestion d''entreprise HES Complément au Master in European Business HES Complément au Master in Accounting and Finance HES Kommunikationswissenschaft und Medienforschung: Bachelornebenfach (60 ECTS) Communication et médias: branche complémentaire Bachelor (30 ECTS) Business Communication - économie politique: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Business Communication - gestion d''entreprise: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Business Communication - informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Business Communication - informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) pr BSc INF Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:18.098523','2017-05-06 13:27:18.098523');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 17 (Semester Course)','Sustainable Globalization',NULL,'Globalization comes in many forms: final goods trade, international outsourcing, international capital flows, international migration of labor, international protection of intellectual property, and international technology transfer. There are a variety of concerns associated with these fundamental changes. Critics argue that some of these patterns affect the sustainability of economic and human development in an undesired fashion. For instance, does liberalization of goods trade and financial markets harm the environment and promote child labor in developing countries? Does international outsourcing of production enhance economic insecurity of workers? Does international migration harm developing countries by triggering brain drain? Does immigration in advanced countries lead to more crime and higher housing costs?','6610-0499','English','Grossmann V.','Helfer F.  Email : fabienne.helfer@unifr.ch','Master',3,4.5,'The goal of the seminar is to obtain a deeper understanding of the consequences of globalization for sustainable economic and human development. We aim at a close connection between theoretical hypotheses and empirical evidence on causal relationships.','Information is regularly updated on Moodle.','each year',NULL,'No restriction','Not authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'Continuous evaluation: Die Notenvergabe erfolgt aufgrund der Leistungen in der mndlichen Mitarbeit (20 Prozent der Gesamtnote), einer schriftlichen Seminararbeit (40 Prozent der Gesamtnote) und einem Vortrag whrend des Seminars (40 Prozent der Gesamtnote).Im Falle einer ungengenden Note muss das Seminar komplett wiederholt werden.',NULL,'English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; Module 2: Economic Policy Master in Economics; Module 3: Economic Sustainability and Development Master in Economics; Module 5: International Economics Master in Economics; Offer Master list Economics Master in Management; EUGB: European and Global Business Master in Management; Module 8: European Business (EUB) Master in European Business; EUGB: European and Global Business Master in European Business; Module European Business (EUB) Ethics and Economics: 30 ECTS Minor Master; Module II : conomie et thique Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:18.101361','2017-05-06 13:27:18.101361');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SA 17 (cours semestriel)','Télévision et vidéo en ligne (II)','Television and online Video','Ce cours est tourn vers la pratique et propose aux tudiants de raliser leur propre reportage en suivant le parcours classique de la construction d''un sujet tlvis: tournage, criture du commentaire et montage, pose de voix, puis mise en ligne. Se rendre sur le terrain, camra au poing, permet d''tre  confront  des situations concrtes de tournage. Rdiger le commentaire forme  l''criture audiovisuelle. Un logiciel permet ensuite de monter son propre sujet. Il suffit de regarder le succs du support vido, pour se rendre compte que la capacit  crer un produit audiovisuel constitue aujourd''hui un atout fortement valoris.','6640-1353','français','Zimmerli V.',NULL,'Bachelor',2,3.0,'Former l''tudiant  construire un reportage tlvis: apprendre les codes pour l''criture d''un produit audiovisuel, se rendre sur le terrain pour recueillir des images et monter son sujet.','Mouriquand Jacques, Pratique du documentaire tlvis, Victoires Editions, 2004Besse Brigite, Desmormeaux Didier, Construire le reportage tlvis, Victoires Editions, 2011Manier Paul-Stphane, Le journalisme audiovisuel: les techniques rdactionnelles en tlvision et sur Internet, INA, 2011','chaque anne',NULL,'20','Pas autorisés','t','Etudiants Erasmus pas admis au cours / sminaires avec un nombre limit de participants, sauf si exception accorde par le professeur sur demande de ltudiant.','Toutes les inscriptions vont tre sur la liste d''attente.Le dpartement communication et des mdias va dcider qui peut suivre ce cours. Avoir suivi le cours Tlvision (I) n''est pas obligatoire, l''enseignant fera un point avec les tudiants qui n''ont pas suivi ce niveau en dbut de semestre.','Rglement du 19 mai 2014 sur l''organisation des tudes et des examens  la Facult des sciences conomiques et sociales de l''Universit de Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'Evaluation continue: Rattrapage possible: examen oral 15 min',NULL,'français','Valable pour les programmes suivants: Kommunikationswissenschaft und Medienforschung: Hauptfach (120 ECTS); Wahlvorlesungen Kommunikationswissenschaft Préalable au Master in Business Communication Communication et médias: branche complémentaire Bachelor (30 ECTS) Business Communication - économie politique: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Business Communication - gestion d''entreprise: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Business Communication - informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Business Communication - informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) pr BSc INF','2017-05-06 13:27:18.104148','2017-05-06 13:27:18.104148');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 17 (Semester Course)','The audit profession and the public interest',NULL,'The topic of the course are legal and professional standards regulating the audit profession in Switzerland and internationally. Major focus is placed on the role of the auditor, ethics, independence as well as responsibility and fraud.','6620-0217','English','Noesberger T.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'The course covers the various influences on the audit profession. A major focus is placed on the role of the auditor in the current environment, ethics, independence as well as responsibility and liability. After the course a student should be able to follow the current discussions regarding the audit function.','Rick Hayes( 2nd Edition, 2004) : Principles of Auditing: An Introduction to International Standards on Auditing FT Prentice Hall, ISBN 0-273-68410-8 /  International Auditing and Assurance Standards Board: Handbook of International Quality Control, Auditing Review, Other Assurance, and Related Services Pronouncements, vol. 1+2, free download from the website of the International Federation of Accountants (www.ifac.org)','each year',NULL,'No restriction','Not authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'oral exam: Only dictionnary allowed','15 Min','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Management; ACC: Accounting and Control Master in Management; Module 5: Accounting and Control (ACC) Master in Accounting and Finance; ACC: Accounting and Control Master in Accounting and Finance; Module Accounting and Control (ACC) Master in European Business; ACC: Accounting and Control Master in European Business; Module Accounting and Control (ACC) Master in Informationsmanagement Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:18.107020','2017-05-06 13:27:18.107020');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 17 (Semester Course)','Mergers & Acquisitions',NULL,'The course covers different aspects of mergers & acquisitions. It starts by giving an overview of M&A activities, strategies and due diligence processes. This is complemented by the valuation of target companies and the financing of M&A deals. It further describes takeover contests and defenses, presents laws and regulations and finishes by post-merger integration strategies.','6620-0543','English','Weisskopf J.-Ph.',NULL,'Master',3,4.5,'This course introduces different concepts related to corporate mergers and acquisitions (M&A). The objective is to give students skills that are necessary to structure a deal or form an opinion about a proposed transaction. The course is relevant for students seeking a career in investment banking, consulting, private equity, or the corporate sector.','Weston, J.F., Mitchell, M.L., Mulherin, J.H. (2004): Takeovers, restructuring, and corporate governance, 4th edition, UppersSaddleRiver.Bruner, Robert F. (2004): Applied Mergers & Acquisitions, Hoboken.Gaughan, Patrick A. (2011): Mergers, Acquisitions, and Corporate Restructurings, 5th Ed., Hoboken.','every 2 years',NULL,'No restriction','Not authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'written exam','60 Min','English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; FIN: Finance Master in Economics; Module 9: Finance Master in Management; ACC: Accounting and Control Master in Management; FIN: Finance Master in Management; Module 4: Finance (FIN) Master in Management; Module 5: Accounting and Control (ACC) Master in Accounting and Finance; ACC: Accounting and Control Master in Accounting and Finance; FIN: Finance Master in Accounting and Finance; Module Accounting and Control (ACC) Master in Accounting and Finance; Module Finance (FIN) Master in European Business; ACC: Accounting and Control Master in European Business; FIN: Finance Master in European Business; Module Accounting and Control (ACC) Master in European Business; Module Finance (FIN) Master in Informationsmanagement Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:18.110365','2017-05-06 13:27:18.110365');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'AS 17 (Semester Course)','The Economics of Politics',NULL,'The economics of politics is the application of economic theory to political processes (Political Economics). Political actors are treated like any other individuals who maximize their utility in any possible interaction. In recent years this approach has proven to provide valuable insights into policymaking and its resulting economic and social outcomes. In this course students learn to use economics in the context of policymaking and interpret and empirical findings. They are introduced to the basic approaches to understand voting and elections, political institutions and their influence on policy outcomes, political actors and their incentives as well as a selection of important topics related to political decision-making such as the influence of the media or corruption, etc. The course combines basic economic theory with empirical research approaches to understand real-world mechanisms. Students are expected to prepare the reading assignments before class in order to participate in class discussions and academic discourse.','6610-0511','English','Schelker M.','Berset S.  Email : simon.berset@unifr.ch','Master',3,4.5,'- Application of economic theory to political processes and real-world politics.- Develop the understanding of basic insights in political economics.- Evaluation of empirical designs.- Participation in class discussions and academic discourse.',NULL,'-',NULL,'No restriction','Not authorised','t','Authorised','-','Regulations from May 19th, 2014 on the organisation of assessments at the Faculty of Economics and Social Sciences of the University of Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'oral exam','15 Min','French; German; English','Valid for the following programmes: Master in Economics; Module 1: Public Economics and Public Finance Master in Economics; Module 3: Economic Sustainability and Development Master in Economics; Offer Master list Economics Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:18.113410','2017-05-06 13:27:18.113410');
INSERT INTO "courses" VALUES(NULL,'SA 17 (cours semestriel)','Systèmes d''informations','Information Systems','Le cours systmes dinformation est une introduction aux systmes dinformation des entreprises, ainsi qu leur modlisation. La premire partie du cours prsente quelques types de systmes dinformation. Larchitecture des systmes oprationnels (OLTP) et des systmes danalyse est dcrite (OLAP) afin de mieux comprendre leur fonctionnement. Les architectures orientes services (SOA) sont traites dun point de vue du business. En plus les architectures des applications mobiles et architectures Cloud sont expliques.La deuxime partie du cours traite de la conception de systmes dinformation (requirements engineering). Quelques diagrammes du langage de modlisation Unified Modeling Language (UML) pertinents pour lexpression des exigences seront prsents. Lobjectif est dacqurir les connaissances ncessaires pour de futurs business analysts/requirements engineer. Le cours est trs interactif et vivant tout en illustrant des aspects d''exemples pratiques, qui sont prsents entre autre par des intervenants externes de haut niveau. Permettant ainsi aux tudiants de se connecter avec de futurs employeurs.','6650-0147','français','Melching M.','Menoud G.  email : gael.menoud@unifr.ch','Bachelor',4,6.0,'Le cours a les objectifs principaux suivants:- Expliquer ce quest un SI et montrer comment diffrents types de SI sont utiliss dans les entreprises - Transmettre aux tudiants les connaissances ncessaires pour jouer le rle danalyste dans un projet de construction de systmes dinformation - Transmitter l''influence de la numrisation (digitalization)','Laudon, K. and Laudon, J. (2018): Management Information Systems: Managing the Digital Firm. Global Edition, 15th edition. Pearson Education Limited. ISBN 9780134639956Morley, C., Hugues, J. et Leblanc, B. (2008) UML 2 pour l''analyse d''un systme d''information - Le cahier des charges du matre d''ouvrage. Dunod, 4e dition, Paris. ISBN 978-2100520978','chaque anne',NULL,'Pas de restrictions','Autorisés','t','Autorisés','-','Rglement du 19 mai 2014 sur l''organisation des tudes et des examens  la Facult des sciences conomiques et sociales de l''Universit de Fribourg',NULL,NULL,'épreuve écrite: Rsum sur une feuille A4 recto-verso crit  la main','90 min','français','Valable pour les programmes suivants: Bachelor en gestion d''entreprise Bachelor en informatique de gestion Informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (30 ECTS) Informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) pr BSc INF Business Communication - informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) Business Communication - informatique de gestion: branche complémentaire Bachelor (60 ECTS) pr BSc INF Benefri-Konvention Wirtschaftswissenschaften','2017-05-06 13:27:18.117037','2017-05-06 13:27:18.117037');
